♪ <i>That's right on time
It's tricky</i> ♪

60
00:06:49,618 --> 00:06:51,787
Watch out. Excuse me.
Pardon me. Coming through.

61
00:06:51,870 --> 00:06:53,497
[song continues playing]

62
00:06:53,581 --> 00:06:55,457
Good evening, gentlemen. Mind if I drive?

63
00:06:55,541 --> 00:06:57,876
- [tires squealing]
- [screaming]

64
00:06:57,960 --> 00:06:59,336
Better buckle up.

65
00:07:01,005 --> 00:07:02,798
[robbers screaming]

66
00:07:07,052 --> 00:07:08,846
How we doing back there?

67
00:07:09,847 --> 00:07:11,390
And now this way.

68
00:07:11,473 --> 00:07:12,516
[grunting]

69
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:13,934
[Sonic laughing]

70
00:07:14,685 --> 00:07:16,812
Whoo-hoo!

71
00:07:17,396 --> 00:07:20,274
[muffled shouting]

72
00:07:20,357 --> 00:07:22,401
Oh, I'm sorry. I don't speak duct tape.

73
00:07:22,484 --> 00:07:23,527
[grunts]

74
00:07:23,611 --> 00:07:26,071
- What the heck are you?
- Fear not, citizen.

75
00:07:26,155 --> 00:07:30,159
I am the hero you need
and the hero you deserve.

76
00:07:30,242 --> 00:07:32,703
The blue dawn that banishes the darkest...

77
00:07:32,786 --> 00:07:34,371
Holy crap!

78
00:07:34,455 --> 00:07:35,456
[both screaming]

79
00:07:35,539 --> 00:07:37,666
[tires squealing]

80
00:07:37,750 --> 00:07:39,043
- [screaming]
- Don't worry.

81
00:07:39,126 --> 00:07:40,711
Nobody's gonna get hurt.

82
00:07:45,507 --> 00:07:47,593
- Huh. What are those?
- Bombs. Bombs.

83
00:07:47,676 --> 00:07:49,053
They're bombs! Those are bombs!

84
00:07:49,136 --> 00:07:51,305
Relax. They're not even lit.

85
00:07:51,388 --> 00:07:55,184
So I'll say again, nobody's gonna get...

86
00:07:55,267 --> 00:07:56,393
[screams] I was wrong!

87
00:07:56,477 --> 00:07:57,811
- We're all gonna die!
- [whimpering]

88
00:08:00,397 --> 00:08:01,774
Why aren't you slowing down?

89
00:08:01,857 --> 00:08:03,609
That would require brakes.

90
00:08:05,277 --> 00:08:08,364
Oh, it's hot. Hot, hot, hot!

91
00:08:08,447 --> 00:08:10,157
Why don't you just let
the police handle this?

92
00:08:10,240 --> 00:08:13,202
Because that's not what heroes do.

93
00:08:16,121 --> 00:08:19,166
Thank you very much.
Please hold your applause.

94
00:08:20,542 --> 00:08:22,127
[horns honking]

95
00:08:22,211 --> 00:08:23,337
[fuse sizzling]

96
00:08:23,420 --> 00:08:26,340
Do you hear that? There's one bomb left.

97
00:08:26,423 --> 00:08:27,925
Uh... Uh-oh.

98
00:08:28,759 --> 00:08:29,885
Did you check under the seat?

99
00:08:29,968 --> 00:08:31,387
Of course I checked under the seat!

100
00:08:32,054 --> 00:08:33,263
[horn honking]

101
00:08:33,347 --> 00:08:34,973
You are terrible at this!

102
00:08:35,057 --> 00:08:37,976
You know what? Your negative attitude
is not helping anyone.

103
00:08:38,060 --> 00:08:40,020
It's in your spiky things!

104
00:08:41,355 --> 00:08:44,441
Ha! I can never find anything in here.
[grunts]

105
00:08:45,609 --> 00:08:48,779
Drained it from downtown! [mimics fanfare]

106
00:08:48,862 --> 00:08:50,739
See? I told you nobody would get hurt.

107
00:08:52,032 --> 00:08:53,826
[people chattering]

108
00:08:53,909 --> 00:08:55,703
Holy sherbet!

109
00:08:57,788 --> 00:08:58,956
Oh, hello.

110
00:08:59,039 --> 00:09:01,750
Don't panic. This is only a drill.

111
00:09:02,668 --> 00:09:05,587
[drill whirring]

112
00:09:05,671 --> 00:09:06,839
[people exclaiming]

113
00:09:12,386 --> 00:09:16,014
[guard screaming]

114
00:09:17,766 --> 00:09:19,893
[breathing shakily]

115
00:09:26,734 --> 00:09:27,735
[fuse sizzling]

116
00:09:29,862 --> 00:09:30,863
[gasps]

117
00:09:41,081 --> 00:09:43,167
- [sirens wailing]
- [tires screech]

118
00:09:43,959 --> 00:09:45,043
Come here!

119
00:09:45,127 --> 00:09:47,880
No need to thank me, citizens.

120
00:09:47,963 --> 00:09:50,090
All in a night's work for...

121
00:09:50,924 --> 00:09:53,510
Blue Justice!

122
00:09:53,594 --> 00:09:55,387
You're a terrible hero!

123
00:09:55,471 --> 00:09:58,056
[Sonic laughing]

124
00:09:58,140 --> 00:09:59,349
["Stars In The Sky" playing]

125
00:09:59,683 --> 00:10:01,894
♪ <i>The feelings running deep</i> ♪

126
00:10:01,977 --> 00:10:03,854
♪ <i>Ain't no time for sleep</i> ♪

127
00:10:03,937 --> 00:10:07,232
♪ <i>A second to unwind
Head up in the sky</i> ♪

128
00:10:07,316 --> 00:10:08,317
[Sonic] Morning, Wade!

129
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:09,526
Morning, Sonic!

130
00:10:09,610 --> 00:10:13,322
[song continues playing]

131
00:10:14,448 --> 00:10:17,159
[Sonic] Whoo-hoo-hoo-hoo-hoo!

132
00:10:17,242 --> 00:10:19,995
Good morning, Green Hills!

133
00:10:29,087 --> 00:10:30,088
[grunting]

134
00:10:30,172 --> 00:10:32,257
Ah! Oop! Oh.

135
00:10:33,050 --> 00:10:34,468
[sighs]

136
00:10:34,551 --> 00:10:37,930
- [floor creaking]
- [groaning]

137
00:10:38,013 --> 00:10:40,057
- [floor creaks louder]
- Oh, come on.

138
00:10:41,683 --> 00:10:43,936
Uh-oh. Uh...

139
00:10:50,692 --> 00:10:51,902
[gasps]

140
00:11:01,286 --> 00:11:02,371
[inaudible]

141
00:11:02,454 --> 00:11:04,122
Oh, Sonic.

142
00:11:04,206 --> 00:11:05,874
I miss you, Longclaw.

143
00:11:06,959 --> 00:11:08,544
I'm trying to make you proud.

144
00:11:17,094 --> 00:11:21,640
[yawning] And now for a little shut-eye.

145
00:11:23,225 --> 00:11:24,226
[lapping]

146
00:11:24,309 --> 00:11:25,727
Oh! Blech!

147
00:11:25,811 --> 00:11:27,521
Ozzy, morning breath!

148
00:11:27,604 --> 00:11:29,523
Sonic. Are you still in bed?

149
00:11:29,606 --> 00:11:32,067
You're supposed to meet Tom, remember?

150
00:11:32,150 --> 00:11:33,694
[grunts]

151
00:11:33,777 --> 00:11:37,406
All right, all right, I'm up! I'm up.

152
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:40,117
[Tom sighs] What a day.

153
00:11:40,701 --> 00:11:42,619
Whoo!

154
00:11:42,703 --> 00:11:44,830
Thanks for coming out, bud.

155
00:11:44,913 --> 00:11:46,498
You know, I feel like you and me,

156
00:11:46,582 --> 00:11:48,500
we haven't had much time together lately.

157
00:11:51,044 --> 00:11:53,171
How's it going over there?
You getting any bites?

158
00:11:53,255 --> 00:11:55,549
[snoring]

159
00:12:00,137 --> 00:12:02,681
[screams] I can't swim! Help!

160
00:12:02,764 --> 00:12:04,433
If I die, don't look in my closet!

161
00:12:04,516 --> 00:12:07,227
Hey, hey, you're good.
You're all right. Come on.

162
00:12:07,311 --> 00:12:08,645
[shivering] It's freezing.

163
00:12:08,729 --> 00:12:10,939
All right, okay. Take it easy.

164
00:12:11,023 --> 00:12:12,441
[shivering]

165
00:12:12,524 --> 00:12:14,735
All right. You're good. Okay.

166
00:12:18,572 --> 00:12:21,450
But now that you've had a nap and a bath...

167
00:12:21,533 --> 00:12:25,579
<i>I went up to your room last night
to bring you some new comics and, um...</i>

168
00:12:30,125 --> 00:12:31,877
[Sonic on tape] <i>Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Stop right there.</i>

169
00:12:31,960 --> 00:12:33,378
<i>I wouldn't come any closer,</i>

170
00:12:33,462 --> 00:12:36,006
<i>because this little hedgehog
had way too many chilidogs.</i>

171
00:12:36,089 --> 00:12:37,966
<i>Oh, no. Oh, no.</i> [farts]

172
00:12:38,050 --> 00:12:40,218
<i>I'm so embarrassed. Get out of here quick!</i>

173
00:12:40,302 --> 00:12:42,554
<i>Oh, no, here comes another one! [farts]</i>

174
00:12:42,638 --> 00:12:44,514
<i>Go. Now. Save yourself.</i>

175
00:12:44,598 --> 00:12:46,141
[tape rewinds] <i>Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Stop right there.</i>

176
00:12:46,224 --> 00:12:47,434
<i>I wouldn't come any closer,</i>

177
00:12:47,517 --> 00:12:50,604
[distorting] <i>because this little hedgehog
had way too many chilidogs.</i>

178
00:12:50,687 --> 00:12:52,522
<i>Oh, no. Oh, no.</i> [farts]

179
00:12:52,606 --> 00:12:54,358
<i>I'm so embarrassed. Get out of here...</i>

180
00:12:54,441 --> 00:12:56,610
Ugh! I knew I should've used real farts.

181
00:12:59,696 --> 00:13:01,365
How many times are we gonna do this?

182
00:13:01,448 --> 00:13:03,992
What? Cast your line and
not catch anything? Seems like a billion.

183
00:13:04,076 --> 00:13:06,411
I think you know what I'm talking about.

184
00:13:06,495 --> 00:13:08,872
The lying. The sneaking out.

185
00:13:08,956 --> 00:13:10,374
The pretending to be Batman.

186
00:13:10,457 --> 00:13:12,042
Blue Justice, trademark pending.

187
00:13:12,125 --> 00:13:13,335
Whatever. You're being reckless.

188
00:13:13,418 --> 00:13:15,629
Ugh! Not this conversation again.

189
00:13:15,712 --> 00:13:17,381
Hey. It's no fun for me, either.

190
00:13:17,464 --> 00:13:18,840
But if you keep being irresponsible,

191
00:13:18,924 --> 00:13:20,550
we're gonna keep having this conversation.

192
00:13:20,634 --> 00:13:22,427
How is it irresponsible to use my powers?

193
00:13:22,511 --> 00:13:25,555
Sonic, you destroyed an entire city block!

194
00:13:25,639 --> 00:13:27,224
That block was already messed up.

195
00:13:27,307 --> 00:13:28,558
Who cares?

196
00:13:28,642 --> 00:13:32,187
Look, I stopped a robbery. I was a hero.

197
00:13:32,270 --> 00:13:35,190
No, you put people in danger
and that's not what a hero does.

198
00:13:37,651 --> 00:13:40,696
[sighs] You're supposed to be my friend.

199
00:13:40,779 --> 00:13:42,155
Stop trying to be my dad.

200
00:13:43,532 --> 00:13:44,783
[sighs]

201
00:13:47,202 --> 00:13:49,079
I can take care of myself.

202
00:13:49,162 --> 00:13:51,623
Sonic, taking care of yourself

203
00:13:51,707 --> 00:13:53,750
is not what being a hero's all about.

204
00:13:53,834 --> 00:13:55,919
It's about taking responsibility
for other people.

205
00:13:57,212 --> 00:13:59,214
And right now,
whether you want to hear this or not,

206
00:13:59,297 --> 00:14:00,340
you are still just a kid.

207
00:14:00,424 --> 00:14:02,718
You got some more growing up to do

208
00:14:02,801 --> 00:14:04,761
before you're ready to be the big hero.

209
00:14:05,721 --> 00:14:07,180
But trust me when I tell you,

210
00:14:07,264 --> 00:14:09,725
there will come a time
when your powers will be needed.

211
00:14:11,601 --> 00:14:13,562
But you don't choose that moment.

212
00:14:14,604 --> 00:14:16,314
That moment chooses you.

213
00:14:16,398 --> 00:14:19,317
Whoa. Look at you. [chuckles]

214
00:14:19,401 --> 00:14:22,154
Look at that. I just got goose bumps.

215
00:14:22,237 --> 00:14:23,989
Wait a second.
Did you steal that from Oprah?

216
00:14:24,072 --> 00:14:27,117
No, sir. That is
a Wachowski family special.

217
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:28,827
Came from my dad,

218
00:14:28,910 --> 00:14:31,038
in this very boat, on this very lake.

219
00:14:32,456 --> 00:14:34,833
He would always try
and steer me in the right direction.

220
00:14:35,709 --> 00:14:37,836
And that's what Maddie and I
have always tried to do with you.

221
00:14:39,087 --> 00:14:42,132
So, until your moment arrives,

222
00:14:43,341 --> 00:14:45,761
I want you to work on
being a little more responsible.

223
00:14:47,220 --> 00:14:48,305
<i>Comprende?</i>

224
00:14:49,097 --> 00:14:50,348
<i>Comprende.</i>

225
00:14:50,432 --> 00:14:51,850
High five on it.

226
00:14:53,226 --> 00:14:56,646
Yeah! Donut Lord and the Blue Blur
are back at it again!

227
00:14:56,730 --> 00:14:58,356
Hang on.

228
00:14:58,440 --> 00:14:59,566
Speedboat!

229
00:14:59,649 --> 00:15:01,318
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

230
00:15:02,903 --> 00:15:04,446
- [Sonic laughing]
- [Tom] Sonic!

231
00:15:04,529 --> 00:15:05,864
[Sonic] Whoo-hoo!

232
00:15:07,032 --> 00:15:08,742
How excited are you,

233
00:15:08,825 --> 00:15:10,786
- going to Hawaii with me?
- Oh, Hawaii.

234
00:15:10,869 --> 00:15:12,871
Oh, yeah! [chuckles]

235
00:15:13,914 --> 00:15:15,624
- Wow.
- [laughs]

236
00:15:15,707 --> 00:15:18,835
Welcome to Sonic Air,
the fastest way to travel.

237
00:15:18,919 --> 00:15:20,295
Now boarding groups one and two.

238
00:15:20,378 --> 00:15:22,756
[laughs] Oh!

239
00:15:22,839 --> 00:15:25,383
Sonic, this is so fun!

240
00:15:25,467 --> 00:15:27,719
I'm sorry, ma'am, you're group three.
Please wait your turn.

241
00:15:27,803 --> 00:15:29,513
Anyone from groups one and two?

242
00:15:29,596 --> 00:15:31,306
- Just let him get it out of his system.
- Nobody?

243
00:15:31,389 --> 00:15:33,642
Okay, then everybody else right this way.

244
00:15:33,725 --> 00:15:34,726
Thank you.

245
00:15:34,810 --> 00:15:38,814
[imitating electronic scanner noises]

246
00:15:38,897 --> 00:15:40,148
[laughs]

247
00:15:40,232 --> 00:15:42,943
And you, sir? [imitating scanner]

248
00:15:43,026 --> 00:15:44,444
Terrible shirt detected.

249
00:15:44,528 --> 00:15:45,612
There we go.

250
00:15:45,695 --> 00:15:47,781
Okay, you're free to go. Enjoy your trip.

251
00:15:47,864 --> 00:15:49,366
Bye-bye now.

252
00:15:49,449 --> 00:15:51,451
- [sighs]
- Okay.

253
00:15:51,535 --> 00:15:52,911
Bring it in.

254
00:15:52,994 --> 00:15:56,331
Tom, I'm about to be
hedgehog of the house for the first time.

255
00:15:56,414 --> 00:15:58,583
I think I'm a little mature
