340
00:19:44,809 --> 00:19:46,144
<i>Stay out of trouble.</i>

341
00:19:46,227 --> 00:19:47,896
Trouble? Don't worry.

342
00:19:47,979 --> 00:19:50,690
Everything here is completely normal.

343
00:19:50,774 --> 00:19:52,192
Uh-huh. Night, bud.

344
00:19:53,234 --> 00:19:55,070
Hey! I was just coming over to say hi.

345
00:19:55,153 --> 00:19:56,738
You've got a lot
of nerve coming up in here

346
00:19:56,821 --> 00:19:58,531
after what you did to my fiancée.

347
00:19:59,366 --> 00:20:01,493
- Wait. What?
- Totaling her car?

348
00:20:01,576 --> 00:20:02,786
Leaving her tied to a chair?

349
00:20:02,869 --> 00:20:04,329
Man, I should rip you limb from limb.

350
00:20:04,412 --> 00:20:06,956
[stammering]

351
00:20:07,040 --> 00:20:08,375
[laughs]

352
00:20:08,458 --> 00:20:10,251
Oh, my God, look at your face!

353
00:20:10,335 --> 00:20:12,253
Tommy, breathe, baby.
Breathe. I was kidding.

354
00:20:12,337 --> 00:20:14,255
- Hey, man, I was totally kidding.
- Okay.

355
00:20:16,132 --> 00:20:17,842
- You were kidding.
- Yeah.

356
00:20:17,926 --> 00:20:19,302
I'm sorry. Rachel put me up to it.

357
00:20:19,386 --> 00:20:21,221
It was totally her idea.

358
00:20:21,304 --> 00:20:22,639
That rascal.

359
00:20:22,722 --> 00:20:24,432
Listen, I don't know if you're aware.

360
00:20:25,392 --> 00:20:26,851
Rachel does not care for you at all.

361
00:20:27,685 --> 00:20:28,937
Oh, I'm aware. Yeah.

362
00:20:29,020 --> 00:20:31,648
Seriously, bro, you got work to do.

363
00:20:31,731 --> 00:20:33,233
- Hey!
- Hey.

364
00:20:33,316 --> 00:20:35,610
Good to see you! Thanks for coming, Tom.

365
00:20:35,693 --> 00:20:37,737
- Really glad you came.
- Really?

366
00:20:38,446 --> 00:20:39,614
Uh... Look,

367
00:20:39,697 --> 00:20:41,741
- great to see you, too. Congratulations.
- Yeah.

368
00:20:41,825 --> 00:20:44,285
I mean, you guys seem
really happy together.

369
00:20:44,369 --> 00:20:45,954
You know, you're all right,
Thomas Wachowski.

370
00:20:46,037 --> 00:20:47,080
Ah.

371
00:20:47,163 --> 00:20:48,790
Can we bury the hatchet?

372
00:20:48,873 --> 00:20:50,250
I'd love that.

373
00:20:50,333 --> 00:20:51,835
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

374
00:20:51,918 --> 00:20:54,379
- All right, bring it in!
- All right! Great.

375
00:20:54,462 --> 00:20:56,673
Oh. [whispering] And if
you screw up my wedding,

376
00:20:56,756 --> 00:20:57,757
I will end you.

377
00:20:59,134 --> 00:21:01,761
[people chattering on TV]

378
00:21:01,845 --> 00:21:04,722
All right, Ozzy, it's movie night
at Casa de Sonic,

379
00:21:04,806 --> 00:21:06,057
and it's your turn to pick.

380
00:21:06,141 --> 00:21:08,685
But I am not watching <i>Snow Dogs</i> again.

381
00:21:08,768 --> 00:21:11,438
That movie is the worst!

382
00:21:11,521 --> 00:21:13,189
