[laughs] Blackout!

384
00:21:16,109 --> 00:21:19,446
- [spooky wailing] Ozzy!
- [Ozzy whines]

385
00:21:19,529 --> 00:21:21,698
Oh, sorry, buddy. Everything's okay.

386
00:21:22,699 --> 00:21:24,033
Whoa!

387
00:21:24,117 --> 00:21:26,244
[static on TV]

388
00:21:28,246 --> 00:21:31,583
Uh, excuse me.
We did not order a poltergeist.

389
00:21:32,625 --> 00:21:35,128
[thunder rumbling]

390
00:21:36,045 --> 00:21:37,881
[electricity buzzing]

391
00:21:38,882 --> 00:21:41,468
[heavy footsteps thudding]

392
00:21:41,551 --> 00:21:45,472
Um, if this is the pizza guy,
this is really unprofessional.

393
00:22:03,323 --> 00:22:04,616
Eggman?

394
00:22:04,699 --> 00:22:05,992
[crackling]

395
00:22:08,119 --> 00:22:11,039
Hello, hedgehog.

396
00:22:12,332 --> 00:22:13,625
Did you miss me?

397
00:22:15,001 --> 00:22:16,586
I don't know how you got back,

398
00:22:16,669 --> 00:22:19,339
but you made a big mistake coming here.

399
00:22:19,422 --> 00:22:22,759
<i>Au contraire, mon frère.</i>

400
00:22:22,842 --> 00:22:25,303
The mistake was thinking you'd won.

401
00:22:25,386 --> 00:22:27,847
But that was just a prelude,
an hors d'oeuvre,

402
00:22:27,931 --> 00:22:30,099
an aperitif, an amuse-bouche.

403
00:22:30,183 --> 00:22:31,476
I get it.

404
00:22:31,559 --> 00:22:33,019
[laughs]

405
00:22:33,102 --> 00:22:34,562
I don't think you do.

406
00:22:34,646 --> 00:22:36,606
But you're about to.

407
