The Master Emerald?

483
00:26:24,500 --> 00:26:26,127
That's just a bedtime story.

484
00:26:26,210 --> 00:26:27,628
Well, he believes it's real.

485
00:26:27,712 --> 00:26:30,006
And he must think
you're the key to finding it.

486
00:26:32,216 --> 00:26:34,051
Red light! Give me the wheel!

487
00:26:34,135 --> 00:26:35,970
- Hey, what are you...
- Move your foot.

488
00:26:37,013 --> 00:26:38,055
[horn honking]

489
00:26:38,139 --> 00:26:40,433
[Sonic yelling]

490
00:26:42,769 --> 00:26:45,021
[sighs] I think we lost him.

491
00:26:48,608 --> 00:26:49,901
[grunts]

492
00:26:52,320 --> 00:26:54,030
[screams] We did not lose him.

493
00:26:54,113 --> 00:26:55,531
We definitely did not lose him!

494
00:26:56,783 --> 00:26:58,034
[whimpers]

495
00:27:00,787 --> 00:27:02,955
I've got an idea. Do you trust me?

496
00:27:03,039 --> 00:27:05,249
Of course not! I literally just met you!

497
00:27:05,333 --> 00:27:07,418
- Just let me... Come on!
- What are you doing?

498
00:27:07,502 --> 00:27:09,587
[Sonic screaming]

499
00:27:11,964 --> 00:27:14,217
[screaming continues]

500
00:27:18,429 --> 00:27:19,764
[grunts]

501
00:27:21,474 --> 00:27:23,893
[whimpering]

502
00:27:26,395 --> 00:27:27,730
We're flying.

503
00:27:27,814 --> 00:27:30,399
Uh, did your butt just
turn into a helicopter?

504
00:27:30,483 --> 00:27:33,402
[laughs] A butt-copter!

505
00:27:33,486 --> 00:27:37,365
Oh, only Sonic the Hedgehog
could come up with something like that.

506
00:27:38,825 --> 00:27:41,661
[tractor engine sputters, dies]

507
00:27:43,621 --> 00:27:45,623
- [grunts]
- [tractor hissing]

508
00:27:50,127 --> 00:27:54,423
[chuckles] Foxy move.

509
00:27:55,883 --> 00:27:57,802
You want something done right...

510
00:27:57,885 --> 00:27:59,136
[electronic beeping]

511
00:27:59,220 --> 00:28:02,223
...you have to hire someone
you can push around.

512
00:28:04,392 --> 00:28:05,309
All caps.

513
00:28:05,643 --> 00:28:07,186
["Don't Know Why" playing]

514
00:28:07,270 --> 00:28:08,771
[whirring]

515
00:28:15,444 --> 00:28:21,742
♪ <i>I waited till saw the sun</i> ♪

516
00:28:21,826 --> 00:28:23,536
♪ <i>I don't know why
I didn't come</i> ♪

517
00:28:23,619 --> 00:28:24,912
Doctor,

518
00:28:25,830 --> 00:28:27,290
where are you?

519
00:28:27,373 --> 00:28:30,126
[song continues playing]

520
00:28:30,209 --> 00:28:31,878
[slams utensil on counter]

521
00:28:33,754 --> 00:28:34,797
Freak.

522
00:28:37,216 --> 00:28:38,634
[sighs]

523
00:28:38,718 --> 00:28:39,802
[watch chimes]

524
00:28:42,513 --> 00:28:44,932
Oh, I, uh... I'm sorry, folks.

525
00:28:45,016 --> 00:28:47,810
Uh, I have to close early. Everybody out!

526
00:28:47,894 --> 00:28:50,980
Everybody out.
Thank you for visiting the Mean Bean.

527
00:28:51,063 --> 00:28:53,107
All right, good night. Good night.

528
00:28:59,906 --> 00:29:01,616
[electronic whirring]

529
00:29:01,699 --> 00:29:04,452
[scanner trilling]

530
00:29:12,293 --> 00:29:13,336
He's back.

531
00:29:15,046 --> 00:29:17,465
He's back!

532
00:29:53,376 --> 00:29:55,169
[drones humming]

533
00:30:02,343 --> 00:30:04,804
[inhales, exhales]

534
00:30:11,811 --> 00:30:14,021
That's more like it.

535
00:30:15,022 --> 00:30:17,858
I've been re-hatched!

536
00:30:20,528 --> 00:30:22,947
[grunting]

537
00:30:23,739 --> 00:30:24,740
[gasps]

538
00:30:26,325 --> 00:30:28,244
[growls]

539
00:30:29,412 --> 00:30:33,958
So, my massively metacarpaled friend,

540
00:30:34,041 --> 00:30:37,169
you mentioned... [howling]

541
00:30:37,253 --> 00:30:39,255
...ultimate power.

542
00:30:39,338 --> 00:30:40,339
Back at the house?

543
00:30:40,423 --> 00:30:42,049
The Master Emerald?

544
00:30:42,133 --> 00:30:43,634
It does not concern you.

545
00:30:43,718 --> 00:30:46,595
I got you off that planet
and you brought me to the hedgehog.

546
00:30:46,679 --> 00:30:48,764
We have no more use for each other.

547
00:30:48,848 --> 00:30:50,933
Well, I hate to be a contrarian, but...

548
00:30:51,017 --> 00:30:52,018
[gloves beep]

549
00:30:52,101 --> 00:30:53,227
...I think we might.

550
00:30:54,729 --> 00:30:57,189
You think these machines
are a match for me?

551
00:30:57,273 --> 00:31:00,735
I will shatter them
like the bones from a fallen...

552
00:31:00,818 --> 00:31:02,737
Oh, they are stairs.

553
00:31:08,451 --> 00:31:13,039
You see, Earth is my turf, G.

554
00:31:13,122 --> 00:31:15,875
If you don't know how to floss,
you'll be lost without me.

555
00:31:15,958 --> 00:31:18,502
I understand nothing
of what you just said.

556
00:31:18,586 --> 00:31:22,965
I help you retrieve the Emerald,
and you use it to...

557
00:31:24,258 --> 00:31:29,388
destroy the hedgehog!

558
00:31:29,472 --> 00:31:31,682
You're suggesting an alliance.

559
00:31:31,766 --> 00:31:35,895
Around here we simply
grip each other's hands tightly.

560
00:31:37,021 --> 00:31:39,565
- [bones cracking]
- Ow, ow, ow, ow, ow!

561
00:31:39,648 --> 00:31:41,192
[gasping]

562
00:31:41,275 --> 00:31:44,904
You truculent space bumpkin!

563
00:31:44,987 --> 00:31:47,156
You've crushed my favorite hand!

564
00:31:47,239 --> 00:31:49,742
Really? My hand is uninjured.

565
00:31:49,825 --> 00:31:50,868
Ugh.

566
00:31:50,951 --> 00:31:53,204
But I'm now convinced of your commitment.

567
00:31:53,287 --> 00:31:55,206
"Oh, goody,"

568
00:31:55,289 --> 00:31:58,793
he exclaimed,
while he reset two of his knuckles.

569
00:31:58,876 --> 00:32:01,212
- [bones crack]
- I'm...

570
00:32:01,295 --> 00:32:06,217
delighted to be on the same team.

571
00:32:14,141 --> 00:32:15,935
Road trip!

572
00:32:16,018 --> 00:32:18,562
I'll let you stick your nose
out the window.

573
00:32:19,647 --> 00:32:22,024
[Tails] Uh, Sonic, where are we?

574
00:32:22,108 --> 00:32:24,485
Welcome to the Wade Cave.

575
00:32:24,568 --> 00:32:27,613
Which is something I hope
to someday say to a woman.

576
00:32:27,696 --> 00:32:29,365
A woman who's not my mom. [chuckles]

577
00:32:29,448 --> 00:32:31,408
Wade, focus.

578
00:32:31,492 --> 00:32:33,202
We need to figure out why Knuckles thinks

579
00:32:33,285 --> 00:32:35,204
I'm the key to finding the Master Emerald.

580
00:32:35,287 --> 00:32:37,706
And why did he mention Longclaw?

581
00:32:37,790 --> 00:32:40,042
There must be a connection.

582
00:32:40,126 --> 00:32:42,461
Wait a minute. There is.

583
00:32:42,545 --> 00:32:46,507
Look. There's an emerald symbol
on the map Longclaw gave me.

584
00:32:46,590 --> 00:32:49,093
I never knew what it meant before.

585
00:32:49,176 --> 00:32:50,845
[Tails] Something's happening.

586
00:32:50,928 --> 00:32:53,722
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

587
00:33:03,983 --> 00:33:05,359
Longclaw?

588
00:33:05,442 --> 00:33:06,986
Hello, Sonic.

589
00:33:07,069 --> 00:33:10,447
If you're watching this,
then something has happened to me.

590
00:33:10,531 --> 00:33:13,784
And I pray you've made it
to Earth unharmed.

591
00:33:13,868 --> 00:33:18,164
This world has been chosen
for a very important reason.

592
00:33:18,247 --> 00:33:22,293
It's the secret location
of the Master Emerald.

593
00:33:22,376 --> 00:33:23,919
Whoa.

594
00:33:24,003 --> 00:33:28,048
The Emerald has the power
to turn thoughts into reality.

595
00:33:28,132 --> 00:33:30,634
Like the Stay Puft Marshmallow Man
from <i>Ghostbusters.</i>

596
00:33:30,718 --> 00:33:31,802
Shh!

597
00:33:31,886 --> 00:33:33,012
In the wrong hands,

598
00:33:33,095 --> 00:33:35,472
it could threaten
all life in the universe.

599
00:33:35,556 --> 00:33:38,475
Protecting the Emerald was my sacred duty.

600
00:33:38,559 --> 00:33:42,229
And now I must pass
that responsibility to you.

601
00:33:43,355 --> 00:33:46,025
This is my moment.

602
00:33:46,108 --> 00:33:49,570
Follow the map, find the Emerald,
and keep it safe.

603
00:33:50,196 --> 00:33:51,739
My dear Sonic,

604
00:33:51,822 --> 00:33:55,326
you have a heart
like no creature I've ever known.

605
00:33:55,409 --> 00:33:57,077
I love you so much.

606
00:33:58,746 --> 00:33:59,955
Goodbye.

607
00:34:01,332 --> 00:34:03,918
No, no, wait. [sighs]

608
00:34:10,257 --> 00:34:12,134
I won't let you down, Longclaw.

609
00:34:14,094 --> 00:34:17,223
So is that y-your dad?

610
00:34:17,306 --> 00:34:18,766
What?

611
00:34:18,849 --> 00:34:19,767
No?

612
00:34:20,100 --> 00:34:21,644
According to this map,

613
00:34:21,727 --> 00:34:23,437
the first clue is in Siberia.

614
00:34:23,520 --> 00:34:25,814
It's a compass that will lead
to the Emerald.

615
00:34:25,898 --> 00:34:28,817
And with Knuckles already here,
it's a race.

616
00:34:28,901 --> 00:34:30,569
Knuckles?

617
00:34:30,653 --> 00:34:32,446
I knew a kid in middle school
named Knuckles.

618
00:34:32,529 --> 00:34:34,365
Could fit his whole fist in his mouth.

619
00:34:34,448 --> 00:34:36,367
If this is the same Knuckles...

620
00:34:36,450 --> 00:34:38,577
[exhales] ...we are screwed.

621
00:34:38,661 --> 00:34:41,080
This Knuckles, that Knuckles.
It doesn't matter.

622
00:34:41,163 --> 00:34:42,831
We're gonna get there first.

623
00:34:44,208 --> 00:34:45,751
[chuckles]

624
00:34:45,834 --> 00:34:47,586
What do you mean, "we"?

625
00:34:47,670 --> 00:34:48,963
You're coming with me.

626
00:34:49,046 --> 00:34:50,381
Oh, no, no, no.

627
00:34:50,464 --> 00:34:53,676
I just came here to warn you.
I'm not a field guy.

628
00:34:53,759 --> 00:34:55,469
Don't worry. I got your back.

629
00:34:55,552 --> 00:34:57,554
I won't let anything happen to you.

630
00:34:59,014 --> 00:35:00,140
It's a power bump.

631
00:35:00,224 --> 00:35:02,768
On Earth, it means an unbreakable promise.

632
00:35:02,851 --> 00:35:05,562
Okay, I'm in.

633
00:35:06,397 --> 00:35:08,440
["Me and You" playing]

634
00:35:08,524 --> 00:35:12,820
♪ <i>Me and you
Maybe sunshine, maybe rain</i> ♪

635
00:35:21,287 --> 00:35:23,664
Doctor. It's really you.

636
00:35:24,581 --> 00:35:26,667
You look different.

637
00:35:26,750 --> 00:35:29,420
Papa's got a brand new 'stache.

638
00:35:30,337 --> 00:35:31,338
Ha!

639
00:35:32,548 --> 00:35:34,174
I knew it. I knew it!

640
00:35:34,258 --> 00:35:36,176
I knew you'd come back, sir.

641
00:35:36,260 --> 00:35:39,263
I never stopped steaming
your Austrian goat's milk.

642
00:35:42,224 --> 00:35:43,559
[Robotnik smacks lips]

643
00:35:44,601 --> 00:35:45,936
Could use some mushroom.

644
00:35:47,813 --> 00:35:48,981
You brought something.

645
00:35:49,064 --> 00:35:52,943
Some kind of, uh, space porcupine.

646
00:35:53,027 --> 00:35:56,030
Porcupine? I am an Echidna!

647
00:35:56,113 --> 00:35:58,699
Trained since birth
in all forms of lethal combat,

648
00:35:58,782 --> 00:36:00,993
destined to restore honor to my tribe,

649
00:36:01,076 --> 00:36:04,872
and willing to destroy
anything that gets in my way.

650
00:36:05,497 --> 00:36:06,874
Welcome to the team.

651
00:36:06,957 --> 00:36:09,084
- [bones cracking]
- [groaning]

652
00:36:09,168 --> 00:36:13,005
- [gasping]
- [laughing]

653
00:36:13,088 --> 00:36:15,549
That means he trusts you, Stone.

654
00:36:15,632 --> 00:36:18,344
Now let's renovate this dump!

655
00:36:18,427 --> 00:36:21,347
Latte with steamed Austrian goat milk!

656
00:36:22,639 --> 00:36:25,309
[machinery whirring]

657
00:36:38,864 --> 00:36:40,366
- [grunts]
- [players cheering]

658
00:36:41,658 --> 00:36:42,910
Good one. Solid.

659
00:36:44,203 --> 00:36:46,955
[grunting]

660
00:36:47,039 --> 00:36:49,708
[players laughing, cheering]

661
00:36:49,792 --> 00:36:51,460
- Sorry, fellas.
- [player] That's game!

662
00:36:51,543 --> 00:36:54,213
Ha! That's how we do! That's how we do!

663
00:36:54,296 --> 00:36:55,464
But are they good at math?

664
00:36:55,547 --> 00:36:57,758
[player] Teamwork makes the dream work!

665
00:36:57,841 --> 00:36:59,676
Sorry about that, Big Tom.

666
00:36:59,760 --> 00:37:01,303
- Are you good?
- All good. Fine.

667
00:37:01,387 --> 00:37:04,932
Hey, thanks for inviting me out
to hang with you and your groomsmen.

668
00:37:05,015 --> 00:37:06,934
Good quality bonding.

669
00:37:07,017 --> 00:37:08,477
You know, bro,

670
00:37:08,560 --> 00:37:10,854
those guys right there,
they're way more than my groomsmen.

671
00:37:10,938 --> 00:37:12,106
That's my squad.

672
00:37:12,189 --> 00:37:14,233
Never would've made it
through life without 'em.

673
00:37:14,316 --> 00:37:15,359
Get over here!

674
00:37:15,442 --> 00:37:17,152
Yeah, I'm coming! I'm coming!

675
00:37:17,236 --> 00:37:18,570
I'll catch you later.

676
00:37:18,654 --> 00:37:20,447
Hey. Yeah!

677
00:37:20,531 --> 00:37:22,825
Let me know if you're ready
for some power yoga, huh?

678
00:37:22,908 --> 00:37:25,953
- You bet.
- Come on, Tommy boy. Let's go.

679
00:37:26,036 --> 00:37:28,080
Don't make me. [laughs]

680
00:37:28,163 --> 00:37:29,248
What am I doing?

681
00:37:29,331 --> 00:37:30,624
Hey, Uncle Tommy!

682
00:37:30,707 --> 00:37:32,209
Hey, girls!

683
00:37:32,292 --> 00:37:33,419
How you do... Oh!

684
00:37:33,502 --> 00:37:35,129
- Are those the wedding rings?
- Uh-huh.

685
00:37:35,212 --> 00:37:36,713
May I?

686
00:37:36,797 --> 00:37:39,758
This little ring bearer
has been taking her job very seriously.

687
00:37:39,842 --> 00:37:41,385
She's been practicing all morning.

688
00:37:41,468 --> 00:37:42,678
I can see that.

689
00:37:42,761 --> 00:37:45,139
How very responsible of you.

690
00:37:45,222 --> 00:37:47,433
Except aren't there supposed
to be two wedding rings?

691
00:37:47,516 --> 00:37:48,642
Uh-oh.

692
00:37:49,560 --> 00:37:50,561
Uncle Tommy?

693
00:37:50,644 --> 00:37:53,313
Hang on. What's going on here?

694
00:37:55,732 --> 00:37:56,942
You're gonna do great, kiddo.

695
00:37:57,025 --> 00:37:58,068
Bye.

696
00:37:58,152 --> 00:37:59,528
- Hey, baby.
- Hi.

697
00:38:00,529 --> 00:38:02,114
- [groomsmen cheering]
- [cork pops]

698
00:38:02,197 --> 00:38:04,658
That's right! Groom in the building!

699
00:38:04,741 --> 00:38:06,201
Look at those guys.

700
00:38:06,285 --> 00:38:08,662
I wish Sonic had that.

701
00:38:08,745 --> 00:38:10,789
- Muscles?
- Control yourself.

702
00:38:10,873 --> 00:38:11,957
Mm-hmm.

703
00:38:12,040 --> 00:38:15,669
No. Buddies. Wingmen. A squad.

704
00:38:15,752 --> 00:38:19,256
Sonic doesn't have anything like that.
He's flying solo.

705
00:38:20,132 --> 00:38:22,092
Baby, you got to relax.

706
00:38:22,176 --> 00:38:24,386
You're at the Four Seasons.

707
00:38:24,470 --> 00:38:27,389
Have a mai tai.
Spend some time with your wife.

708
00:38:27,473 --> 00:38:30,559
That's what he said.
Seriously, his exact words.

709
00:38:30,642 --> 00:38:32,728
- See? He's a smart kid.
- All right.

710
00:38:32,811 --> 00:38:34,688
- Hmm.
- He'll find his way.

711
00:38:34,771 --> 00:38:38,358
- I absolutely cannot find my way.
- [wind howling]

712
00:38:38,442 --> 00:38:41,778
We are completely, totally,
unequivocally lost.

713
00:38:41,862 --> 00:38:43,155
[device beeping]

714
00:38:43,238 --> 00:38:44,698
Sonic, in this weather,

715
00:38:44,781 --> 00:38:47,576
there's no way we're gonna get
any readings on this thing!

716
00:38:47,659 --> 00:38:48,744
Should we go back?

717
00:38:48,827 --> 00:38:50,913
No, no, no. There's a light up ahead.

718
00:38:50,996 --> 00:38:52,956
Maybe we can take shelter in there.

719
00:38:56,835 --> 00:38:59,588
Ah. Perfect.

720
00:38:59,671 --> 00:39:02,841
Are you sure about this?
We don't know who's inside.

721
00:39:02,925 --> 00:39:06,178
Don't worry. On Earth,
people are very welcoming,

722
00:39:06,261 --> 00:39:09,681
and love taking complete strangers
into their homes.

723
00:39:10,098 --> 00:39:13,310
- [people chattering in Russian]
- [up-tempo music playing]

724
00:39:16,522 --> 00:39:19,149
[door creaks open]

725
00:39:19,233 --> 00:39:21,485
[music and chatter stops]

726
00:39:25,155 --> 00:39:26,782
[both gasp]

727
00:39:28,450 --> 00:39:29,660
[both gasp]

728
00:39:31,328 --> 00:39:32,663
[both sigh]

729
00:39:35,374 --> 00:39:36,625
[both scream]

730
00:39:36,708 --> 00:39:38,085
[grunts]

731
00:39:39,753 --> 00:39:40,796
Run.

732
00:39:41,463 --> 00:39:43,298
[groans]

733
00:39:43,382 --> 00:39:45,008
Table for two, please!

734
00:39:47,135 --> 00:39:49,388
What would you like to order?

735
00:39:49,471 --> 00:39:51,139
Two beef stews, please.

736
00:39:51,223 --> 00:39:53,141
[translating into Russian]

737
00:39:56,603 --> 00:39:58,188
Where'd you get all these cool gadgets?

738
00:39:58,272 --> 00:39:59,731
I invented 'em.

739
00:39:59,815 --> 00:40:01,775
That's kinda my thing.

740
00:40:01,858 --> 00:40:04,319
In fact, my inventions
are how I discovered you.

741
00:40:05,153 --> 00:40:07,489
<i>Remember that night at the baseball field?</i>

742
00:40:07,573 --> 00:40:11,285
<i>Your energy blast reached all the way
to my home planet.</i>

743
00:40:11,368 --> 00:40:15,998
I saw you save your whole village
from that crazy mustache guy.

744
00:40:16,081 --> 00:40:19,293
Wait, so you've been
watching me this whole time?

745
00:40:19,376 --> 00:40:20,961
Even in the shower?

746
00:40:21,044 --> 00:40:22,963
That's a trick question.

747
00:40:23,046 --> 00:40:25,257
Sonic the Hedgehog prefers bubble baths.

748
00:40:25,340 --> 00:40:26,675
Man, you're good!

749
00:40:26,758 --> 00:40:29,219
When I learned Knuckles was on your trail,

750
00:40:29,303 --> 00:40:32,139
I knew I couldn't just sit back
and watch anymore.

751
00:40:32,222 --> 00:40:33,682
I had to come warn you.

752
00:40:33,765 --> 00:40:34,850
[phone chimes]

753
00:40:34,933 --> 00:40:36,602
Oh, what? Hang on one sec.

754
00:40:36,685 --> 00:40:38,270
Donut Lord is checking in.

755
00:40:39,813 --> 00:40:44,318
[Knuckles] "Just chilling. Watching TV."

756
00:40:44,401 --> 00:40:46,778
Dot, dot, dot.

757
00:40:46,862 --> 00:40:49,656
Dot, dot, dot.

758
00:40:49,740 --> 00:40:51,450
Dot, dot, dot.

759
00:40:51,533 --> 00:40:53,827
Dot, dot, dot.

760
00:40:53,910 --> 00:40:55,912
Dot, dot, dot.

761
00:40:56,997 --> 00:40:58,040
Doctor,

762
00:40:58,999 --> 00:41:01,209
why are we working with this imbecile?

763
00:41:02,669 --> 00:41:08,091
Because that simpleminded space trash
is the key to something extraordinary.

764
00:41:08,175 --> 00:41:11,136
Something to help you
get revenge on the hedgehog.

765
00:41:11,219 --> 00:41:12,929
Think bigger, Stone.

766
00:41:13,013 --> 00:41:16,308
The emerald he seeks
could power my wildest designs.

767
00:41:16,391 --> 00:41:18,769
My genius wouldn't
just be recognized on Earth.

768
00:41:18,852 --> 00:41:21,855
It would spread virally
to every corner of the galaxy,

769
00:41:21,938 --> 00:41:25,901
allowing me to harness
all the negative forces of the universe

