[Sonic] We are talking style and pizzazz.

1023
00:55:39,337 --> 00:55:42,131
♪ <i>Where it may rain or storm</i> ♪

1024
00:55:42,215 --> 00:55:44,133
Pew-pew-pew! Pew, pew, pew, pew, pew, pew.

1025
00:55:44,217 --> 00:55:45,968
♪ <i>Yet I'm safe and warm</i> ♪

1026
00:55:46,052 --> 00:55:49,222
Yeah! I make this look good.

1027
00:55:50,348 --> 00:55:51,599
[grunts]

1028
00:55:51,682 --> 00:55:53,851
Oh, great. The Winter Soldier.

1029
00:56:00,775 --> 00:56:03,653
For a guy named Knuckles,
you are really bad at punching.

1030
00:56:03,736 --> 00:56:07,031
Surrender the compass!
You are no match for me.

1031
00:56:07,114 --> 00:56:09,700
I've been training for this
my entire life.

1032
00:56:09,784 --> 00:56:13,204
And I had no training at all,
yet here I am ahead of you.

1033
00:56:13,287 --> 00:56:15,373
That's gotta be embarrassing.

1034
00:56:16,874 --> 00:56:18,000
[yelps]

1035
00:56:20,670 --> 00:56:22,755
[gasps] My rings!

1036
00:56:26,092 --> 00:56:29,929
Has anyone ever told you
you've got serious anger issues?

1037
00:56:30,012 --> 00:56:32,139
You mock me with your weak jokes,

1038
00:56:32,223 --> 00:56:34,433
but you know nothing about me, hedgehog.

1039
00:56:34,517 --> 00:56:36,227
Well, I know you Echidnas have a habit of

1040
00:56:36,310 --> 00:56:38,521
showing up uninvited and ruining my life.

1041
00:56:38,604 --> 00:56:42,024
Ruining your life? Another bad joke.

1042
00:56:42,108 --> 00:56:44,944
I lost everything because of you.

1043
00:56:45,027 --> 00:56:48,322
<i>My tribe was on the verge
of its greatest victory.</i>

1044
00:56:48,406 --> 00:56:51,284
<i>The last of the Owl warriors
had been located.</i>

1045
00:56:51,367 --> 00:56:55,121
<i>Soon Longclaw's Emerald secrets
would be ours.</i>

1046
00:56:55,204 --> 00:56:58,416
<i>But my father stopped me
from joining the fight.</i>

1047
00:56:58,499 --> 00:57:02,044
<i>He said my moment
to honor our tribe would come,</i>

1048
00:57:02,128 --> 00:57:04,255
<i>but it was not this moment.</i>

1049
00:57:04,338 --> 00:57:06,966
<i>Those were the last words he spoke to me.</i>

1050
00:57:07,049 --> 00:57:09,385
I never saw him again.

1051
00:57:10,970 --> 00:57:13,472
We both lost everything that day.

1052
00:57:14,724 --> 00:57:15,808
[Echidnas yelling]

1053
00:57:15,891 --> 00:57:17,435
- Goodbye, Sonic.
- No!

1054
00:57:17,518 --> 00:57:19,395
<i>Longclaw!</i>

1055
00:57:21,355 --> 00:57:22,815
[groaning]

1056
00:57:23,691 --> 00:57:25,568
Sonic! Are you okay?

1057
00:57:25,651 --> 00:57:27,361
Deceiver!

1058
00:57:27,445 --> 00:57:30,031
No, no, it wasn't a trick.

1059
00:57:30,114 --> 00:57:32,908
Tails, take the compass
and get out of here!

1060
00:57:36,120 --> 00:57:37,121
Yeah!

1061
00:57:38,497 --> 00:57:40,416
Later, haters!

1062
00:57:43,753 --> 00:57:44,879
Tails!

1063
00:57:52,053 --> 00:57:53,638
Tails, come on. Wake up.

1064
00:57:53,721 --> 00:57:56,390
He chose helping the fox
over pursuing the compass.

1065
00:57:56,474 --> 00:57:57,975
Of course he did.

1066
00:57:58,059 --> 00:58:00,645
New friend, same pathetic weakness.

1067
00:58:01,354 --> 00:58:02,396
Hmm.

1068
00:58:03,147 --> 00:58:05,024
[rumbling]

1069
00:58:05,107 --> 00:58:06,233
[gasps]

1070
00:58:10,946 --> 00:58:13,616
Oh, no. No, no, no.
We're in real trouble here.

1071
00:58:13,699 --> 00:58:16,702
Come on, Tails. I need you
to fly us out of here. Time to wake up.

1072
00:58:24,377 --> 00:58:27,505
See ya, kids. Enjoy the fresh powder.

1073
00:58:29,340 --> 00:58:31,342
[grunting]

1074
00:58:32,718 --> 00:58:34,637
[ukulele music playing]

1075
00:58:37,056 --> 00:58:38,307
[guests murmuring]

1076
00:58:41,811 --> 00:58:44,814
[airplane passing overhead]

1077
00:58:45,773 --> 00:58:48,317
[guests applauding]

1078
00:58:53,030 --> 00:58:54,115
Did you...

1079
00:58:59,620 --> 00:59:02,289
These rings signify the...

1080
00:59:02,373 --> 00:59:04,542
[phone ringtone]

1081
00:59:08,129 --> 00:59:09,797
[laughs] Sorry.

1082
00:59:09,880 --> 00:59:11,424
- Thought it was on silent.
- [ringtone stops]

1083
00:59:18,013 --> 00:59:20,307
- These rings...
- [phone ringtone]

1084
00:59:21,434 --> 00:59:22,727
So help me, Thomas!

1085
00:59:24,061 --> 00:59:26,188
[stammering]

1086
00:59:27,565 --> 00:59:29,024
Okay, sorry. Sorry.

1087
00:59:29,108 --> 00:59:30,651
Excuse me, this is an emergency.

1088
00:59:32,403 --> 00:59:33,946
Sorry.

1089
00:59:36,949 --> 00:59:38,784
[phone ringing]

1090
00:59:38,868 --> 00:59:41,620
What? This better be important. I just...

1091
00:59:41,704 --> 00:59:43,080
<i>Are you skiing?</i>

1092
00:59:43,164 --> 00:59:45,416
<i>Snowboarding, actually.
But I need your help now.</i>

1093
00:59:45,499 --> 00:59:47,835
Life or death situation this very second.

1094
00:59:47,918 --> 00:59:50,838
I need you to use the ring
I gave you to save me. Like right now.

1095
00:59:50,921 --> 00:59:53,174
<i>Okay, slowdown.
I don't even know where you are.</i>

1096
00:59:53,257 --> 00:59:55,468
You just gotta picture
where you want the ring to go.

1097
00:59:55,551 --> 00:59:56,677
So picture this.

1098
00:59:59,472 --> 01:00:02,016
Oh, my God. Okay, okay. Hang on.

1099
01:00:09,982 --> 01:00:11,484
What?

1100
01:00:13,152 --> 01:00:14,445
[Sonic] <i>Did you throw it?</i>

1101
01:00:15,279 --> 01:00:17,740
- Oh, God.
- [Sonic] <i>What? Tellme what "Oh, God."</i>

1102
01:00:17,823 --> 01:00:19,366
I mixed up the rings
when I was teasing Jojo.

1103
01:00:19,450 --> 01:00:20,868
<i>What? Where is it then?</i>

1104
01:00:25,372 --> 01:00:26,457
You don't want to know.

1105
01:00:26,540 --> 01:00:27,875
<i>Oh, but I do, Tom.</i>

1106
01:00:27,958 --> 01:00:29,293
- [sighs]
<i>- I very much want to know,</i>

1107
01:00:29,376 --> 01:00:31,837
before I become
a hedgehog-flavored snow cone.

1108
01:00:31,921 --> 01:00:34,006
Hang tight, buddy. I got this.

1109
01:00:34,089 --> 01:00:35,883
With this ring, Rachel...

1110
01:00:35,966 --> 01:00:37,718
- Hey! Hi.
- [guests gasp]

1111
01:00:37,802 --> 01:00:39,720
- Uh...
- Everything okay, bud?

1112
01:00:39,804 --> 01:00:41,722
- Not really.
- What are you doing?

1113
01:00:41,806 --> 01:00:44,016
This is gonna sound crazy,
but I need to see that ring

1114
01:00:44,099 --> 01:00:46,435
- for just one second.
- Have you lost your mind?

1115
01:00:46,519 --> 01:00:48,312
I'm gonna give it right back, I promise.

1116
01:00:48,395 --> 01:00:51,148
- Please, Randall, it's really important.
- No, bro. Go sit down.

1117
01:00:51,232 --> 01:00:52,233
Give me the ring, please?

1118
01:00:52,316 --> 01:00:54,193
- Randall, don't look at him, look at me.
- Randall.

1119
01:00:54,276 --> 01:00:55,861
- One second.
- Put the ring on my finger.

1120
01:00:55,945 --> 01:00:57,488
No, Randall, listen to me.

1121
01:00:57,571 --> 01:00:59,281
Randall! Look at me. Ring on my finger.

1122
01:00:59,365 --> 01:01:01,826
- Give me the ring! Just one second.
- Put a ring on it!

1123
01:01:02,576 --> 01:01:03,953
Please, love? Okay?

1124
01:01:04,036 --> 01:01:05,037
- With this ring...
- Yes, baby.

1125
01:01:05,120 --> 01:01:06,872
I'm so sorry about this.

1126
01:01:06,956 --> 01:01:08,541
- [grunts]
- [guests exclaiming]

1127
01:01:10,793 --> 01:01:12,294
[grunts]

1128
01:01:13,379 --> 01:01:14,839
[gasps]

1129
01:01:17,049 --> 01:01:19,176
- Snow, my God.
- Oh, boy.

1130
01:01:19,969 --> 01:01:21,387
Incoming!

1131
01:01:21,470 --> 01:01:22,471
[guests screaming]

1132
01:01:25,933 --> 01:01:27,351
[Sonic] Oh.

1133
01:01:28,978 --> 01:01:31,939
[guests groaning, chattering]

1134
01:01:32,940 --> 01:01:34,358
Anybody hurt?

1135
01:01:34,441 --> 01:01:36,485
- Sonic!
- Ah, Hawaii.

1136
01:01:36,569 --> 01:01:37,820
Are you okay?

1137
01:01:37,903 --> 01:01:39,780
- What's happening? Are you hurt?
- [groaning]

1138
01:01:39,864 --> 01:01:41,824
- No, no, I'm fine.
- Okay, good.

1139
01:01:41,907 --> 01:01:43,367
Because you're in so much trouble!

1140
01:01:43,450 --> 01:01:45,452
Okay, you calm down.

1141
01:01:45,536 --> 01:01:46,871
You talk.

1142
01:01:46,954 --> 01:01:48,372
Okay, quick version.

1143
01:01:48,455 --> 01:01:51,000
Robotnik is back on Earth
and he's after a magic emerald.

1144
01:01:51,083 --> 01:01:52,167
[grunts, sighs]

1145
01:01:52,251 --> 01:01:55,337
We need to get it back
or the world is doomed.

1146
01:01:56,046 --> 01:01:57,172
Tails!

1147
01:01:57,256 --> 01:01:59,466
Wait! All this happened since yesterday?

1148
01:01:59,550 --> 01:02:00,718
Wait. Wait. Who's Tails?

1149
01:02:00,801 --> 01:02:02,052
Tails, can you hear me?

1150
01:02:02,136 --> 01:02:04,096
Oh, Lord, there are two of them now.

1151
01:02:04,179 --> 01:02:06,348
Okay, let me think. Tails, come on, buddy.

1152
01:02:06,432 --> 01:02:08,767
[Sonic groaning]

1153
01:02:09,560 --> 01:02:11,020
[weapons powering up]

1154
01:02:11,103 --> 01:02:12,479
Hey!

1155
01:02:12,563 --> 01:02:14,732
Randall, why do all of your friends
have weapons?

1156
01:02:16,817 --> 01:02:18,986
You really should have
taken me up on that brunch,

1157
01:02:19,069 --> 01:02:20,070
Mr. and Mrs. Wachowski.

1158
01:02:20,738 --> 01:02:21,906
Olive Garden guy?

1159
01:02:21,989 --> 01:02:25,117
It's okay, everyone. We're federal agents.

1160
01:02:25,200 --> 01:02:27,786
You, too, Agent. Go ahead.

1161
01:02:34,293 --> 01:02:35,920
You mean to tell me

1162
01:02:36,003 --> 01:02:39,089
- that this entire wedding was a setup?
- Rachel, wait a minute.

1163
01:02:39,173 --> 01:02:40,174
What?

1164
01:02:40,257 --> 01:02:41,342
That's correct, ma'am.

1165
01:02:41,425 --> 01:02:43,218
Every single aspect of Operation Catfish

1166
01:02:43,302 --> 01:02:44,803
was a complete fabrication.

1167
01:02:45,971 --> 01:02:47,389
Operation Catfish?

1168
01:02:47,473 --> 01:02:49,850
So is everyone here an agent?

1169
01:02:51,226 --> 01:02:52,394
Are you an agent?

1170
01:02:53,228 --> 01:02:54,813
Son of a...

1171
01:02:54,897 --> 01:02:58,233
Was the florist an agent?
How about the photographer?

1172
01:02:58,317 --> 01:03:00,361
The woman who waxed my...

1173
01:03:01,362 --> 01:03:02,446
at the spa?

1174
01:03:04,073 --> 01:03:05,115
Is Jojo an agent?

1175
01:03:05,199 --> 01:03:06,450
[Randall] Rachel.

1176
01:03:06,533 --> 01:03:07,993
What?

1177
01:03:08,077 --> 01:03:09,119
Rachel, listen to me.

1178
01:03:09,203 --> 01:03:10,454
I'm done listening!

1179
01:03:10,537 --> 01:03:12,706
I am done listening!

1180
01:03:12,790 --> 01:03:15,834
- I am so sorry. I am so sorry.
- [sobbing]

1181
01:03:15,918 --> 01:03:17,503
I really am. I am so sorry.

1182
01:03:19,463 --> 01:03:21,507
No. Hey, no!

1183
01:03:22,466 --> 01:03:24,093
Let him go! Hey!

1184
01:03:26,720 --> 01:03:27,721
[grunts]

1185
01:03:27,805 --> 01:03:29,515
Sonic, hang on.

1186
01:03:29,598 --> 01:03:31,016
Take it easy. It's not worth it.

1187
01:03:31,100 --> 01:03:32,810
- Tom!
- Ah-ah-ah.

1188
01:03:32,893 --> 01:03:35,479
Sonic is not a threat. He's on our side.

1189
01:03:35,562 --> 01:03:37,481
He's an uncontrolled extraterrestrial.

1190
01:03:37,564 --> 01:03:39,650
And your days of aiding
and abetting him are over.

1191
01:03:39,733 --> 01:03:42,444
Secure them in the hotel
until the chopper arrives.

1192
01:03:42,528 --> 01:03:44,446
You're making a mistake.

1193
01:03:44,530 --> 01:03:46,615
[Rachel] Hold on, Major A-hole!

1194
01:03:46,699 --> 01:03:48,325
This is still my day,

1195
01:03:48,409 --> 01:03:52,121
and someone is gonna explain to me
what the hell is going on here!

1196
01:03:52,204 --> 01:03:53,664
After the events in San Francisco,

1197
01:03:53,747 --> 01:03:55,541
a global task force was created,

1198
01:03:55,624 --> 01:03:58,836
devoted to protecting
our planet from alien threats.

1199
01:03:58,919 --> 01:04:01,588
That day,
Guardian Units of Nations was born.

1200
01:04:01,672 --> 01:04:04,258
- G-U-N. Seriously?
- GUN, yeah.

1201
01:04:04,341 --> 01:04:06,927
Look, what about protecting
our planet from Dr. Robotnik?

1202
01:04:08,262 --> 01:04:09,638
Robotnik is dead.

1203
01:04:09,722 --> 01:04:11,807
You're wrong. He's back.

1204
01:04:11,890 --> 01:04:14,309
And you just hauled away
the only ones who could stop him.

1205
01:04:17,104 --> 01:04:19,064
Sounds like Robotnik
might be back in play.

1206
01:04:19,148 --> 01:04:21,650
If he is, I want him found immediately.

1207
01:04:22,985 --> 01:04:25,571
And cancel my five o'clock
at the Olive Garden.

1208
01:04:25,654 --> 01:04:27,281
- Aunt Maddie?
- Yeah.

1209
01:04:27,364 --> 01:04:29,033
Sonic and his friend dropped this.

1210
01:04:31,285 --> 01:04:33,495
[gadgets beeping]

1211
01:04:35,873 --> 01:04:37,291
I have an idea.

1212
01:04:37,374 --> 01:04:39,543
And I want to have a word with my fiancé.

1213
01:04:39,626 --> 01:04:41,253
And that word is "murder."

1214
01:04:45,924 --> 01:04:48,761
[Sonic] Hey, come on.
You can't just leave us in here.

1215
01:04:48,844 --> 01:04:51,972
My friend is hurt!
He needs a doctor, a vet, anyone!

1216
01:04:53,307 --> 01:04:54,767
Tails, you got to wake up, buddy.

1217
01:04:54,850 --> 01:04:56,727
Buddy, please wake up.

1218
01:04:57,811 --> 01:04:59,313
[children chattering, laughing]

1219
01:05:02,441 --> 01:05:03,776
[police radio chatter]

1220
01:05:03,859 --> 01:05:05,652
[on radio] <i>All clear.</i>

1221
01:05:09,281 --> 01:05:10,866
All right. Game plan.

1222
01:05:10,949 --> 01:05:13,911
I get inside the hotel and find
where they're hiding Tom and Sonic.

1223
01:05:13,994 --> 01:05:15,621
Okay. Then I find Randall, right?

1224
01:05:15,704 --> 01:05:17,122
And then I squeeze the breath

1225
01:05:17,206 --> 01:05:21,293
from his lying, deceitful,
perfectly manscaped body!

1226
01:05:21,376 --> 01:05:23,587
[cackles]

1227
01:05:23,670 --> 01:05:25,380
I'm going through a lot right now.

1228
01:05:25,464 --> 01:05:27,174
So let me process this my own way, okay?

1229
01:05:27,257 --> 01:05:28,550
- Sure, sure.
- Okay.

1230
01:05:28,634 --> 01:05:30,844
- No judgment.
- Should've brought a journal.

1231
01:05:30,928 --> 01:05:32,304
Okay...

1232
01:05:32,387 --> 01:05:35,933
Okay. Is this meant to be a weapon?
This is adorable.

1233
01:05:36,016 --> 01:05:38,143
Pew, pew! Take that, Randall!

1234
01:05:38,227 --> 01:05:40,270
[imitates explosion] Run, Randall!

1235
01:05:40,354 --> 01:05:41,772
All right.

1236
01:05:41,855 --> 01:05:43,774
- I guess we're about to find out.
- All right!

1237
01:05:43,857 --> 01:05:46,068
Let's go kick some booty. [laughs]

1238
01:05:48,278 --> 01:05:49,822
[Maddie] Shh! Shh!

1239
01:05:59,164 --> 01:06:00,624
Rachel! No. Rachel!

1240
01:06:01,917 --> 01:06:03,001
In a minute.

1241
01:06:04,128 --> 01:06:05,546
Mm-mmm! Mm.

1242
01:06:08,715 --> 01:06:10,300
Stop right there!

1243
01:06:10,384 --> 01:06:11,593
Get the bag.

1244
01:06:14,221 --> 01:06:15,305
[device beeping]

1245
01:06:16,765 --> 01:06:18,267
[screaming]

1246
01:06:19,810 --> 01:06:21,353
He's gonna come back down, right?

1247
01:06:21,436 --> 01:06:22,896
- I don't know.
- [groans]

1248
01:06:22,980 --> 01:06:23,981
Good luck!

1249
01:06:26,150 --> 01:06:28,485
Look. Tom and Sonic have to be inside.

1250
01:06:28,569 --> 01:06:30,988
- I got a fiancé to vaporize.
- Uh-huh.

1251
01:06:31,071 --> 01:06:32,573
- Watch your back, sis.
- Okay.

1252
01:06:32,656 --> 01:06:35,367
[both grunting, growls]

1253
01:06:35,450 --> 01:06:36,451
Randall!

1254
01:06:40,622 --> 01:06:41,707
[grunts]

1255
01:06:43,542 --> 01:06:44,585
We got her.

1256
01:06:45,544 --> 01:06:46,712
Move in.

1257
01:06:49,923 --> 01:06:50,924
Okay.

1258
01:06:56,221 --> 01:06:57,514
[grunts]

1259
01:06:57,598 --> 01:06:58,932
[grunts]

1260
01:06:59,016 --> 01:07:00,142
[grunts]

1261
01:07:07,232 --> 01:07:09,151
I did not mean to do that!

1262
01:07:11,320 --> 01:07:13,113
Whoo!

1263
01:07:21,872 --> 01:07:23,874
Something bothering you, Agent?

1264
01:07:23,957 --> 01:07:26,627
I just feel a little guilty
about what I did to Rachel, sir.

1265
01:07:26,710 --> 01:07:30,005
Ah, don't worry about it.
We'll send her a gift card.

1266
01:07:30,088 --> 01:07:32,216
Now, I propose a toast.

1267
01:07:35,427 --> 01:07:38,222
To a perfectly executed operation.

1268
01:07:38,305 --> 01:07:39,765
[agent screaming]

1269
01:07:42,893 --> 01:07:44,561
Sir, we're under attack.

1270
01:07:44,645 --> 01:07:46,063
["Barracuda" playing]

1271
01:07:46,146 --> 01:07:48,315
- [crashing]
- [glass shattering]

1272
01:07:53,403 --> 01:07:55,614
[crashing continues]

1273
01:08:04,915 --> 01:08:09,169
Randall, wifey's home! [cackles]

1274
01:08:13,131 --> 01:08:14,758
Oh, my God. Rachel.

1275
01:08:16,843 --> 01:08:19,096
♪ <i>You lying so low
In the weeds</i> ♪

1276
01:08:19,179 --> 01:08:20,681
[tires screeching]

1277
01:08:20,764 --> 01:08:22,891
♪ <i>I bet you gonna ambush me</i> ♪

1278
01:08:23,558 --> 01:08:29,106
♪ <i>You'd have me down, down
Down, down on my knees</i> ♪

1279
01:08:29,189 --> 01:08:31,483
♪ <i>Now wouldn't you, barracuda?</i> ♪

1280
01:08:34,069 --> 01:08:35,821
♪ <i>Oh</i> ♪

1281
01:08:39,449 --> 01:08:42,286
What a woman.

1282
01:08:44,454 --> 01:08:45,664
You no-good,

1283
01:08:46,915 --> 01:08:49,918
lowdown, dirty, lying...

1284
01:08:50,002 --> 01:08:51,211
Rachel, just listen to me.

1285
01:08:51,295 --> 01:08:52,921
What kind of twisted sicko

1286
01:08:53,005 --> 01:08:55,549
tricks someone into a fake wedding?

1287
01:08:55,632 --> 01:08:57,342
[weapon clicks, powers up]

1288
01:08:57,426 --> 01:09:00,595
Party's over, Bridezilla.
Stop right there.

1289
01:09:01,513 --> 01:09:03,640
You son of a...

1290
01:09:03,724 --> 01:09:05,892
- Have it your way.
- No!

1291
01:09:05,976 --> 01:09:07,602
- No!
- [electrodes buzzing]

1292
01:09:08,228 --> 01:09:10,147
[groaning]

1293
01:09:10,230 --> 01:09:12,441
Oh. Ugh. Oh!

1294
01:09:12,524 --> 01:09:14,860
Very disappointing, Agent Handel.

1295
01:09:17,195 --> 01:09:19,323
Ha! Is that supposed to be a weapon?

1296
01:09:19,406 --> 01:09:21,199
I don't know, but we gonna find out.

1297
01:09:21,283 --> 01:09:23,702
Haven't you caused
enough trouble for one day?

1298
01:09:23,785 --> 01:09:26,663
Oh, I haven't even begun causing trouble.

1299
01:09:26,747 --> 01:09:29,875
Hell hath no fury like a bride scorned.

1300
01:09:36,715 --> 01:09:40,177
Looks like it's real, huh? [laughs]

1301
01:09:41,303 --> 01:09:43,180
Whoa! Uh! Ah! Huh?

1302
01:09:43,263 --> 01:09:44,598
No. Right.

1303
01:09:46,516 --> 01:09:49,102
Be honest. How bad is it?

1304
01:09:49,186 --> 01:09:52,314
Not bad at all.
You got Tased. You'll be fine.

1305
01:09:56,443 --> 01:09:57,444
I'm so cold.

1306
01:09:57,527 --> 01:10:00,322
You landed on our ice sculpture.

1307
01:10:00,405 --> 01:10:01,490
Get up.

1308
01:10:07,579 --> 01:10:09,122
Just...

1309
01:10:09,206 --> 01:10:12,084
Just tell me the truth, for once.

1310
01:10:13,126 --> 01:10:17,422
Is there anything about you
or about us that was real?

1311
01:10:18,215 --> 01:10:21,551
Rachel, look at me.

1312
01:10:22,719 --> 01:10:23,887
Before I met you,

1313
01:10:23,970 --> 01:10:26,515
I didn't think that I was even capable
of real happiness.

1314
01:10:28,183 --> 01:10:30,852
But that all changed
when you walked into my life.

1315
01:10:30,936 --> 01:10:34,314
And I ended up breaking
the first rule of undercover work.

1316
01:10:35,023 --> 01:10:36,400
Which is?

1317
01:10:36,483 --> 01:10:38,527
Never fall in love.

1318
01:10:49,413 --> 01:10:51,206
[door lock beeps, clicks]

1319
01:10:51,289 --> 01:10:52,874
- [Tom] Maddie!
- [Sonic] Maddie!

1320
01:10:52,958 --> 01:10:55,669
- We're busting out of here.
- How'd you get past the guards?

1321
01:10:55,752 --> 01:10:57,587
Because that little fox
is into some crazy stuff.

1322
01:10:57,671 --> 01:11:00,215
- Come on.
- [laughing]

1323
01:11:00,298 --> 01:11:01,842
- Let's go.
- You're amazing.

1324
01:11:12,644 --> 01:11:15,313
The Owls were fools to think
they could hide this.

1325
01:11:23,613 --> 01:11:25,031
Ah.

1326
01:11:28,368 --> 01:11:30,245
[chiming]

1327
01:11:30,328 --> 01:11:32,247
[rumbling]

1328
01:11:53,185 --> 01:11:54,936
What's happening?

1329
01:11:56,563 --> 01:11:58,231
Wait for it.

1330
01:12:03,445 --> 01:12:05,489
[exclaims]

1331
01:12:05,572 --> 01:12:09,701
[cackling]

1332
01:12:09,784 --> 01:12:12,037
Yes. Eureka!

1333
01:12:13,246 --> 01:12:14,956
I've found it!

1334
01:12:23,548 --> 01:12:24,966
[explosion]

1335
01:12:34,434 --> 01:12:35,560
Sonic.

1336
01:12:37,521 --> 01:12:39,272
- What is that?
- A big problem.

1337
01:12:40,315 --> 01:12:42,234
The compass led Robotnik to the Emerald.

1338
01:12:42,317 --> 01:12:44,319
That's got to be hundreds of miles away.

1339
01:12:45,779 --> 01:12:47,239
All right.

1340
01:12:47,322 --> 01:12:49,199
Huddle up. Let's figure out a plan.

1341
01:12:49,282 --> 01:12:50,325
Together.

1342
01:12:50,408 --> 01:12:51,701
There's no time for that.

1343
01:12:51,785 --> 01:12:53,745
I'm the only one
that can get there fast enough.

1344
01:12:53,828 --> 01:12:56,331
Sonic, this is way too big
for you to do by yourself.

1345
01:12:56,414 --> 01:12:58,416
You see that little fox over there?

1346
01:12:58,500 --> 01:13:02,003
He came all the way
across the universe to meet his hero.

1347
01:13:02,087 --> 01:13:05,006
And what did his hero do?
I practically got him killed.

1348
01:13:05,882 --> 01:13:08,301
You know what? You were right.

1349
01:13:08,385 --> 01:13:10,595
My moment came and I blew it.

1350
01:13:10,679 --> 01:13:11,972
I'm no hero.

1351
01:13:12,055 --> 01:13:13,223
- Wait.
- [Sonic] No.

1352
01:13:13,306 --> 01:13:15,809
I'm not letting anyone else get hurt
because of me.

1353
01:13:15,892 --> 01:13:17,602
I'm gonna fix this while I still can.

1354
01:13:19,104 --> 01:13:20,730
- Sonic!
- [gasps]

1355
01:13:20,814 --> 01:13:23,149
Sonic, wait! [grunts]

1356
01:13:23,233 --> 01:13:24,985
[groaning]

1357
01:13:25,068 --> 01:13:27,862
- Hold on. Wait. Don't move.
- Hey, hey, hey.

1358
01:13:27,946 --> 01:13:29,531
Take it easy, little guy. You're hurt.

1359
01:13:29,614 --> 01:13:33,285
But we have to help him.
You don't know what he's up against.

1360
01:13:40,500 --> 01:13:41,876
You believe us now?

1361
01:13:43,878 --> 01:13:45,505
Mm-hmm.

1362
01:13:45,589 --> 01:13:47,173
[siren wailing]

1363
01:13:47,257 --> 01:13:48,925
["You Know How We Do It" playing]

1364
01:13:49,009 --> 01:13:50,093
Hey, Bob!

1365
01:13:50,176 --> 01:13:51,928
- Hey, Maria, how you doing?
- Hey!

1366
01:13:52,012 --> 01:13:53,138
Ah.

1367
01:13:55,307 --> 01:13:56,516
Working on my moves.

1368
01:13:56,600 --> 01:13:59,227
Just keepin' it green.
No need to burn the fuel.

1369
01:13:59,311 --> 01:14:01,229
Speaking of fuel... [groans]

1370
01:14:06,735 --> 01:14:09,487
Closed? [sighs]

1371
01:14:09,571 --> 01:14:10,905
That doesn't seem right.

1372
01:14:16,036 --> 01:14:18,747
[electronic beeping]

1373
01:14:23,710 --> 01:14:24,753
Close.

1374
01:14:29,299 --> 01:14:30,592
Yes.

1375
01:14:30,675 --> 01:14:33,219
Makeover, makeover. Look at you.

1376
01:14:33,303 --> 01:14:34,638
Freeze! Police!

1377
01:14:36,014 --> 01:14:38,099
Oh, my God, you got robot hands.

1378
01:14:38,183 --> 01:14:39,434
No, they're gloves.

1379
01:14:39,517 --> 01:14:41,561
Get 'em up. Now spread your fingers!

1380
01:14:42,896 --> 01:14:45,523
Now wiggle 'em! Wiggle your digits!

1381
01:14:46,983 --> 01:14:49,653
Yes! Like you just finished
a big musical number.

1382
01:14:51,488 --> 01:14:53,031
Good.

1383
01:14:53,114 --> 01:14:54,532
Why is there a light on your head?

1384
01:14:58,453 --> 01:15:00,497
'Cause I'm the sheriff
for the weekend, pal.

1385
01:15:08,797 --> 01:15:10,590
[Sonic] Ugh. Water.

1386
01:15:10,674 --> 01:15:12,550
Why did it have to be water?

1387
01:15:14,302 --> 01:15:15,387
[exhales]

1388
01:15:15,470 --> 01:15:18,306
Okay, you can do this.

1389
01:15:21,643 --> 01:15:23,520
I gotta go fast.

1390
01:15:43,498 --> 01:15:46,459
[grunting]

1391
01:15:47,585 --> 01:15:49,045
[Sonic yells]

1392
01:15:50,046 --> 01:15:52,382
[yelling]

1393
01:15:59,055 --> 01:16:01,683
[panting]

1394
01:16:01,766 --> 01:16:04,644
[straining]

1395
01:16:20,201 --> 01:16:21,786
[coughing]

1396
01:16:32,380 --> 01:16:34,549
[gasps]

1397
01:16:53,276 --> 01:16:54,611
Oh!

1398
01:16:57,822 --> 01:16:59,073
[grunts]

1399
01:17:06,122 --> 01:17:09,459
I don't want to die like this!
It's derivative!

1400
01:17:11,002 --> 01:17:12,670
Make room for Daddy!

1401
01:17:14,464 --> 01:17:15,757
[grunting]

1402
01:17:20,637 --> 01:17:22,680
Two and two. Great!

1403
01:17:22,764 --> 01:17:25,558
- We're still bipedals, more or less.
- [sighs]

1404
01:17:28,436 --> 01:17:29,979
Fire in the hole!

1405
01:17:32,190 --> 01:17:35,401
I've solved it. There is a booby trap
every seven seco...

1406
01:17:42,075 --> 01:17:44,118
- That was a little early.
- Mmm.

1407
01:17:44,202 --> 01:17:48,540
Oh! So glad it didn't cut off my mustache.

1408
01:17:48,623 --> 01:17:51,793
Hey, Little Red Wrecking Ball.

1409
01:17:51,876 --> 01:17:54,212
I know you're dying
to get your Emerald on,

1410
01:17:54,295 --> 01:17:58,424
but can we be a little bit more mindful
of our surroundings?

1411
01:17:58,508 --> 01:17:59,551
May I?

1412
01:17:59,634 --> 01:18:00,927
[glove beeping]

1413
01:18:06,182 --> 01:18:08,768
[electronic voice] <i>In 30feet, turn left.</i>

1414
01:18:08,852 --> 01:18:10,728
Work smarter, not harder.

1415
01:18:25,368 --> 01:18:28,329
[Sonic yelling]

1416
01:18:29,497 --> 01:18:32,083
[grunting, groans]

1417
01:18:32,166 --> 01:18:33,543
My pelvis.

1418
01:18:37,922 --> 01:18:42,051
Okay, Secret Temple,
let's see what you've got.

1419
01:18:48,308 --> 01:18:50,268
Whoa!

1420
01:18:50,351 --> 01:18:51,853
No, no, no! No!

1421
01:18:52,437 --> 01:18:54,147
[yells]

1422
01:18:54,230 --> 01:18:56,482
[exclaiming]

1423
01:18:56,566 --> 01:18:57,567
No.

1424
01:18:58,735 --> 01:19:00,653
Yes! [screams]

1425
01:19:05,700 --> 01:19:07,619
[electronic voice]
<i>You have arrived at your destination.</i>

1426
01:19:07,702 --> 01:19:10,788
Wow. That really opened up the space.

1427
01:19:10,872 --> 01:19:13,750
I can't even picture it
with an impenetrable wall now.

1428
01:19:13,833 --> 01:19:15,752
And the rubble is always a nice touch.

1429
01:19:24,969 --> 01:19:28,681
At last. The Master Emerald.

1430
01:19:28,765 --> 01:19:30,016
Ultimate power.

1431
01:19:30,099 --> 01:19:32,936
Soon order will be restored.

1432
01:19:33,019 --> 01:19:36,356
All because of what we have done together.

1433
01:19:36,439 --> 01:19:39,150
Such a lovely sentiment, Knuckles.

1434
01:19:39,233 --> 01:19:41,819
I think I feel a single tear forming.

1435
01:19:44,781 --> 01:19:46,032
Sadly...

1436
01:19:46,115 --> 01:19:47,116
[crackling]

1437
01:19:47,200 --> 01:19:48,451
...you're as useful to me now

1438
01:19:48,534 --> 01:19:51,579
as a backstage pass to Limp Bizkit.

1439
01:19:52,538 --> 01:19:54,874
- [thudding]
- [Sonic yelling] Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

1440
01:19:54,958 --> 01:19:56,209
[Sonic yelling]

1441
01:19:58,169 --> 01:20:00,338
[yelling continues]

1442
01:20:00,421 --> 01:20:02,382
- [metal clanking]
- [Sonic grunting]

1443
01:20:02,465 --> 01:20:04,550
[yells, grunts]

1444
01:20:04,634 --> 01:20:06,302
[coughing]

1445
01:20:06,386 --> 01:20:07,387
Nailed it.

1446
01:20:07,470 --> 01:20:08,596
[gasps]

1447
01:20:08,680 --> 01:20:12,892
This guy is always trying
to spoil a bad thing!

1448
01:20:12,976 --> 01:20:14,602
Ah! You guys are here, too?

1449
01:20:14,686 --> 01:20:16,062
Took the long way, huh?

1450
01:20:16,145 --> 01:20:18,314
Is everything a joke to you?

1451
01:20:18,398 --> 01:20:21,359
Why must you constantly interfere
with my destiny?

1452
01:20:21,442 --> 01:20:25,113
Because my destiny
is to protect my friends and family.

1453
01:20:25,196 --> 01:20:27,365
I think I just threw up in my mouth.

1454
01:20:27,448 --> 01:20:33,371
And if you want that emerald,
you're gonna have to go through me.

1455
01:20:34,205 --> 01:20:35,289
[gulps]

1456
01:20:38,918 --> 01:20:40,211
Whoa!

1457
01:20:44,882 --> 01:20:46,009
[both yelling]

1458
01:20:47,218 --> 01:20:49,303
[both grunting]

1459
01:20:55,643 --> 01:20:58,688
The Echidna's taking no prisoners today!

1460
01:20:58,771 --> 01:21:02,525
Sonic has heart,
but will he lose the quill to live?

1461
01:21:04,360 --> 01:21:08,031
I don't want to fight you,
but you're not giving me much choice.

1462
01:21:10,324 --> 01:21:13,453
[grunting]

1463
01:21:13,536 --> 01:21:17,498
[grunts] Too easy. Let's do this.

1464
01:21:23,129 --> 01:21:24,505
Huh?

1465
01:21:24,589 --> 01:21:25,715
[grunts]

1466
01:21:34,307 --> 01:21:36,893
[both grunting]

1467
01:21:41,647 --> 01:21:42,732
[yelling]

1468
01:21:42,815 --> 01:21:44,567
[grunting]

1469
01:21:44,650 --> 01:21:49,072
Why don't you stand still
and die with honor?

1470
01:21:49,155 --> 01:21:50,406
Let me think about it.

1471
01:21:50,490 --> 01:21:54,160
Okay, I thought about it and I pass.

1472
01:21:54,243 --> 01:21:55,828
[yelling]

1473
01:22:03,628 --> 01:22:05,088
Hi there, beautiful.

1474
01:22:06,380 --> 01:22:08,883
You're the real deal, aren't you?

1475
01:22:09,092 --> 01:22:12,512
Where have you been all my life?

1476
01:22:13,679 --> 01:22:16,265
[groaning]

1477
01:22:16,349 --> 01:22:18,768
Say goodbye, hedgehog.

1478
01:22:18,851 --> 01:22:20,186
[gasps]

1479
01:22:22,271 --> 01:22:25,191
Knuckles, stop.
Robotnik's stealing the Emerald!

1480
01:22:25,274 --> 01:22:27,735
What kind of fool do you take me for?

1481
01:22:27,819 --> 01:22:29,070
Just look.

1482
01:22:31,614 --> 01:22:32,949
Mine.

1483
01:22:34,200 --> 01:22:36,911
Wait! That wasn't the deal.

1484
01:22:36,994 --> 01:22:38,246
[boulder thuds]

1485
01:22:39,080 --> 01:22:42,917
Oh, you poor, naive creature.

1486
01:22:43,000 --> 01:22:44,669
It's not your fault.

1487
01:22:44,752 --> 01:22:48,214
A more advanced intellect would have
seen this move coming a mile away.

1488
01:22:48,297 --> 01:22:50,550
Or 1.6 kilometers.

1489
01:22:50,633 --> 01:22:53,386
But I trusted you! You were my friend!

1490
01:22:53,469 --> 01:22:56,639
[cackling]

1491
01:23:00,351 --> 01:23:02,812
I'm sorry. That just hit me funny.

1492
01:23:03,855 --> 01:23:06,357
Let this be my final lesson to you,

1493
01:23:06,440 --> 01:23:08,901
you dim-witted celestial skin tag.

1494
01:23:09,861 --> 01:23:11,237
Friends...

1495
01:23:11,320 --> 01:23:15,324
are open, honest
and vulnerable with each other.

1496
01:23:15,408 --> 01:23:17,952
Which means X squared
times the hypotenuse of Y squared,

1497
01:23:18,035 --> 01:23:21,289
divided by the absolute value
of friendship, equals...

1498
01:23:21,372 --> 01:23:22,415
dookie!

1499
01:23:22,498 --> 01:23:23,749
Oh, no.

1500
01:23:28,754 --> 01:23:29,964
[Sonic, Knuckles scream]

1501
01:23:31,883 --> 01:23:36,804
Chaos is power!

1502
01:23:36,888 --> 01:23:38,890
[yelling]

1503
01:23:55,698 --> 01:23:56,949
Let's get out of here!

1504
01:23:57,033 --> 01:23:58,367
[gasps]

1505
01:24:09,503 --> 01:24:10,671
Knuckles!

1506
01:24:15,134 --> 01:24:18,012
Water again? Come on!

1507
01:24:27,980 --> 01:24:29,523
[straining]

1508
01:24:34,111 --> 01:24:35,529
[Sonic growls]

1509
01:24:35,613 --> 01:24:37,698
[straining]

1510
01:24:37,782 --> 01:24:40,034
- Mmm?
- [grunts]

1511
01:24:40,117 --> 01:24:41,994
- [muffled exclaiming]
- Mmm?

1512
01:24:42,078 --> 01:24:43,704
Mmm. Mmm.

1513
01:24:44,789 --> 01:24:45,957
Mmm?

1514
01:24:49,752 --> 01:24:53,005
[muffled yelling]

1515
01:24:54,215 --> 01:24:56,008
[Sonic grunting]

1516
01:24:56,842 --> 01:24:59,804
[muffled grunting]

1517
01:25:04,016 --> 01:25:05,810
[groaning]

1518
01:25:14,068 --> 01:25:16,654
[coughing]

1519
01:25:16,737 --> 01:25:17,863
You saved me.

1520
01:25:17,947 --> 01:25:20,741
Don't talk to me. I'm not in the mood.

1521
01:25:20,825 --> 01:25:22,076
[grunts]

1522
01:25:22,159 --> 01:25:25,705
How dare you attack me
in my hour of sorrow!

1523
01:25:25,788 --> 01:25:26,956
[grunts]

1524
01:25:27,039 --> 01:25:28,499
Why did you save me?

1525
01:25:29,458 --> 01:25:30,459
[grunts]

1526
01:25:30,543 --> 01:25:32,378
Because you saved me first,

1527
01:25:32,461 --> 01:25:36,132
which clearly gave you
a tactical advantage I do not understand.

1528
01:25:36,215 --> 01:25:39,844
It wasn't a tactic.
I couldn't just let you die.

1529
01:25:40,886 --> 01:25:42,096
Why?

1530
01:25:42,179 --> 01:25:45,599
I've been trying to destroy you
since the moment we met.

1531
01:25:45,683 --> 01:25:49,603
Because being a hero
isn't about taking care of yourself.

1532
01:25:49,687 --> 01:25:53,107
It's about taking responsibility
for other people.

1533
01:25:54,442 --> 01:25:58,654
Hmm. Wise words. An ancient Earth proverb?

1534
01:25:58,738 --> 01:26:01,157
No, sir, that's
a Wachowski family special.

1535
01:26:01,240 --> 01:26:03,909
I got it from a guy in a rowboat.

1536
01:26:03,993 --> 01:26:05,494
Someone who means a lot to me.

1537
01:26:05,578 --> 01:26:07,330
[biplane approaching]

1538
01:26:07,413 --> 01:26:08,998
Wait a second. What's that sound?

1539
01:26:11,167 --> 01:26:14,670
Only Sonic the Hedgehog
needs rescuing this much.

1540
01:26:14,754 --> 01:26:17,715
[laughs] That sly little fox!

1541
01:26:20,259 --> 01:26:23,346
Come on, Knucklehead. We're not beat yet.

1542
01:26:23,429 --> 01:26:25,931
On the mountain,
you told me you'd lost everything.

1543
01:26:26,015 --> 01:26:28,059
The way I did.

1544
01:26:28,142 --> 01:26:31,187
But you seem so hopeful and free.

1545
01:26:31,270 --> 01:26:35,483
How did you move forward
despite failing again?

1546
01:26:35,566 --> 01:26:39,362
And again. And again.
And again. And again.

1547
01:26:39,445 --> 01:26:43,074
Okay, I didn't fail that much.
But I didn't do this all alone.

1548
01:26:43,157 --> 01:26:45,743
I found a new family. New friends.

1549
01:26:45,826 --> 01:26:47,244
And you can too.

1550
01:26:49,538 --> 01:26:51,957
You don't have to be alone anymore.

1551
01:26:55,086 --> 01:26:57,171
- [bones cracking]
- [Sonic] Ow! Ow! Ow! Ow!

1552
01:26:57,254 --> 01:26:59,340
Are you kidding me with that handshake?

1553
01:27:01,842 --> 01:27:03,844
[Wade] I'm done playing games, pal.

1554
01:27:04,929 --> 01:27:06,680
You're gonna tell me what I want to know.

1555
01:27:09,100 --> 01:27:12,478
And I am asking you for the last time...

1556
01:27:14,814 --> 01:27:17,274
what would you like on your bagel?

1557
01:27:17,358 --> 01:27:19,276
I'm not telling you anything.

1558
01:27:19,360 --> 01:27:22,279
And that is a display bagel.

1559
01:27:22,363 --> 01:27:25,574
I don't get it with you!
I mean, I've tried everything.

1560
01:27:25,658 --> 01:27:27,201
I was good cop. I was bad cop.

1561
01:27:27,284 --> 01:27:29,286
I was cop who offers you a bagel.

1562
01:27:29,370 --> 01:27:30,538
And nothing. It's like...

1563
01:27:30,621 --> 01:27:32,706
That is a display bagel. Wow.

1564
01:27:32,790 --> 01:27:34,291
[rumbling]

1565
01:27:34,375 --> 01:27:37,253
[electronic warbling]

1566
01:27:38,212 --> 01:27:39,422
[yells]

1567
01:27:41,966 --> 01:27:43,717
Doctor, you're here.

1568
01:27:45,719 --> 01:27:50,391
[in electronic voice]
Yes, I'm here, and yet I'm...

1569
01:27:51,934 --> 01:27:53,602
not all there.

1570
01:27:53,686 --> 01:27:55,187
Sir, are you feeling okay?

1571
01:27:55,271 --> 01:27:59,942
I'm more than okay.

1572
01:28:00,025 --> 01:28:03,154
I'm upgraded.

1573
01:28:03,237 --> 01:28:06,282
[singsongy] Sinister 3.0.

1574
01:28:06,365 --> 01:28:10,202
My game is next level.

1575
01:28:10,286 --> 01:28:13,956
[warped vocalizing]

1576
01:28:15,458 --> 01:28:16,625
- Hi.
- [screams]

1577
01:28:19,462 --> 01:28:25,634
I can smell the electricity in your brain.

1578
01:28:25,718 --> 01:28:27,386
[sniffs]

1579
01:28:27,470 --> 01:28:29,763
You smell like a snack plate.

1580
01:28:31,182 --> 01:28:34,768
Yeah, no, that's fair.
I had a couple today.

1581
01:28:34,852 --> 01:28:36,312
Sit down.

1582
01:28:40,983 --> 01:28:42,401
In the chair.

1583
01:28:44,987 --> 01:28:46,864
Yeah, no, no, I didn't know.

1584
01:28:47,865 --> 01:28:50,951
'Cause he was in the chair,
so I didn't... Okay.

1585
01:28:51,035 --> 01:28:52,953
Sir? We have a problem.

1586
01:28:58,876 --> 01:29:01,837
- [soldier 1] All teams in position!
- [soldier] Set up a perimeter!

1587
01:29:01,921 --> 01:29:03,464
[soldier] Move! Move! Move!

1588
01:29:18,604 --> 01:29:22,233
<i>Incorrectus,</i> my trusty barnacle.

1589
01:29:23,567 --> 01:29:26,028
After all these years,

1590
01:29:26,695 --> 01:29:28,405
what I finally got...

1591
01:29:29,573 --> 01:29:31,617
is a solution.

1592
01:29:42,253 --> 01:29:44,129
- Commander.
- Status report.

1593
01:29:44,213 --> 01:29:47,675
Robotnik is in there with Stone
and a hostage. Possibly local PD.

1594
01:29:47,758 --> 01:29:51,053
I'm not saying he's dumb,
but if he is local PD,

1595
01:29:51,136 --> 01:29:53,430
this town's in a lot of trouble.

1596
01:29:53,514 --> 01:29:54,807
[both] Wade.

1597
01:30:06,318 --> 01:30:07,903
Um...

1598
01:30:09,196 --> 01:30:10,990
Okay.

1599
01:30:11,073 --> 01:30:13,701
Rockin' that new spring collection, I see.

1600
01:30:13,784 --> 01:30:18,330
Well, if it isn't the Pastry King.

1601
01:30:18,414 --> 01:30:19,957
The Donut Lord.

1602
01:30:20,040 --> 01:30:21,834
A real genius would remember
the name of the guy

1603
01:30:21,917 --> 01:30:23,836
who helped kick your butt off this planet.

1604
01:30:23,919 --> 01:30:25,879
And I'll do it again
if you mess with Green Hills.

1605
01:30:25,963 --> 01:30:30,759
Congratulations on your oh-so-temporary
sense of superiority.

1606
01:30:30,843 --> 01:30:33,178
You're finished, Robotnik!
We've taken everything.

1607
01:30:33,262 --> 01:30:35,973
Your lab, your drones, your funding!

1608
01:30:36,056 --> 01:30:39,226
Let's see how big of a man
you are without your silly little robots.

1609
01:30:40,978 --> 01:30:42,896
Would you like to see how...

1610
01:30:44,356 --> 01:30:46,483
big a man I can be?

1611
01:30:57,369 --> 01:31:00,539
Welcome to the new norm.

1612
01:31:10,841 --> 01:31:12,217
My God!

1613
01:31:15,721 --> 01:31:19,433
Doctor! Take me with you!

1614
01:31:21,352 --> 01:31:23,937
[screaming]

1615
01:31:30,152 --> 01:31:31,779
[train horn blowing]

1616
01:31:43,874 --> 01:31:45,501
He's taking everything apart.

1617
01:31:46,710 --> 01:31:48,128
He's building something.

1618
01:31:56,136 --> 01:31:58,514
[Tails] That can only be one thing.

1619
01:31:58,597 --> 01:32:00,974
The fearsome power of the Emerald.

1620
01:32:01,058 --> 01:32:03,268
If that thing really
turns thoughts into power,

1621
01:32:03,352 --> 01:32:05,187
we are in big trouble.

1622
01:32:05,270 --> 01:32:07,189
Robotnik has a lot of bad thoughts.

1623
01:32:07,272 --> 01:32:10,234
Hey, Sonic, are you sure
it was a good idea

1624
01:32:10,317 --> 01:32:11,819
bringing you-know-who aboard?

1625
01:32:11,902 --> 01:32:15,656
Knuckles isn't really a bad guy.
He's just a little mixed up.

1626
01:32:15,739 --> 01:32:17,449
I am not mixed up!

1627
01:32:17,533 --> 01:32:20,744
I have steely focus. And I'm complex.

1628
01:32:20,828 --> 01:32:22,413
And that's a lot for some people.

1629
01:32:22,496 --> 01:32:25,874
[chuckles] Hope you're not still mad
I hit you with that car.

1630
01:32:25,958 --> 01:32:28,377
Pfft! I was completely uninjured.

1631
01:32:28,460 --> 01:32:31,630
And my revenge will come
when you least expect it, fox.

1632
01:32:58,073 --> 01:32:59,324
Whoa.

1633
01:33:03,078 --> 01:33:05,664
Sir, you're magnificent!

1634
01:33:05,748 --> 01:33:07,791
Thank you, sycophant.

1635
01:33:07,875 --> 01:33:10,294
Your admiration is inevitable.

1636
01:33:20,345 --> 01:33:21,805
I knew it!

1637
01:33:21,889 --> 01:33:24,391
Just like the Stay Puft Marshmallow Man.

1638
01:33:25,476 --> 01:33:27,519
World Domination playlist.

1639
01:33:27,603 --> 01:33:30,063
[heavy metal playing]

1640
01:33:40,866 --> 01:33:42,034
Fall back.

1641
01:33:43,452 --> 01:33:46,288
Fall back! Quick! Retreat!

1642
01:33:48,290 --> 01:33:50,375
How are we supposed to beat this thing?

1643
01:33:50,459 --> 01:33:51,502
We need a plan.

1644
01:33:51,585 --> 01:33:53,420
Knuckles, use your strength to...

1645
01:33:54,213 --> 01:33:56,548
Jump off the plane. Wow.

1646
01:33:56,632 --> 01:34:00,552
Okay, this is what we're gonna do.
Step 1: Light taunting.

1647
01:34:00,636 --> 01:34:02,387
Step 2: I have no idea.

1648
01:34:05,516 --> 01:34:06,683
Sonic!

1649
01:34:09,853 --> 01:34:11,814
[Sonic] Nice action figure, Eggman.

1650
01:34:11,897 --> 01:34:14,817
Does it do anything
or just stand there looking ugly?

1651
01:34:18,487 --> 01:34:20,906
Like a blister, he keeps coming back!

1652
01:34:22,157 --> 01:34:25,118
He's on the okay-to-kill list.
Shoot the missiles. Make a decision.

1653
01:34:25,202 --> 01:34:27,996
I need a moment, sir.
I'm trying to figure out how to do this.

1654
01:34:28,080 --> 01:34:30,165
Did you even glance at a manual?

1655
01:34:30,249 --> 01:34:32,417
- No!
- I'll do it.

1656
01:34:32,501 --> 01:34:33,919
Pardon my lightning.

1657
01:34:34,002 --> 01:34:35,879
- You might want to ground yourself.
- [groaning]

1658
01:34:38,048 --> 01:34:39,049
Uh-oh.

1659
01:34:39,132 --> 01:34:43,011
I'm gonna pop that thing open
like a can of chili... [screams]

1660
01:34:43,095 --> 01:34:44,137
[Sonic] Whoa!

1661
01:34:44,221 --> 01:34:45,681
[Tails] Hang on!

1662
01:34:47,641 --> 01:34:49,560
Whoa!

1663
01:34:49,643 --> 01:34:51,186
[grunting]

1664
01:34:51,979 --> 01:34:54,189
Whoa! [laughs]

1665
01:34:57,067 --> 01:34:58,443
- Whoo!
- Whoo-hoo!

1666
01:34:58,527 --> 01:35:01,113
- Oh, yeah!
- Whoo! Whoo-hoo-hoo! Close one.

1667
01:35:01,196 --> 01:35:03,115
- [Sonic grunts]
- Sonic!

1668
01:35:06,869 --> 01:35:08,453
Robotnik!

1669
01:35:10,080 --> 01:35:11,540
Deceiver!

1670
01:35:11,623 --> 01:35:13,417
Die, mosquito.

1671
01:35:15,544 --> 01:35:16,628
[panting]

1672
01:35:16,712 --> 01:35:17,880
[grunting]

1673
01:35:22,968 --> 01:35:24,928
[yells]

1674
01:35:25,012 --> 01:35:26,847
Ooh! I felt that.

1675
01:35:33,896 --> 01:35:36,940
[growling]

1676
01:35:39,484 --> 01:35:42,029
Oh! Whoa!

1677
01:35:46,033 --> 01:35:47,492
What just happened?

1678
01:35:47,576 --> 01:35:50,829
It's the Stache Masher.
Right here in the manual.

1679
01:35:53,123 --> 01:35:55,459
Return to sender.

1680
01:35:56,793 --> 01:35:58,879
[Robotnik, Stone grunt]

1681
01:36:02,925 --> 01:36:04,051
Stone?

1682
01:36:05,886 --> 01:36:06,887
Oh, great.

1683
01:36:06,970 --> 01:36:10,057
Next thing you know, there'll be a report
about a hostile work environment.

1684
01:36:13,143 --> 01:36:16,313
Those were our best attacks,
and they did nothing!

1685
01:36:16,396 --> 01:36:18,732
We can't beat Robotnik
as long as he's got that Emerald.

1686
01:36:18,815 --> 01:36:20,233
He's too powerful.

1687
01:36:20,317 --> 01:36:23,403
Look, we aren't strong enough
to beat Robotnik on our own.

1688
01:36:23,487 --> 01:36:24,738
But there's three of us.

1689
01:36:24,821 --> 01:36:27,991
Your strength, your smarts and my speed.

1690
01:36:28,075 --> 01:36:29,743
Together. That's how we win.

1691
01:36:29,826 --> 01:36:34,289
So we make our stand here
on the field of battle.

1692
01:36:34,373 --> 01:36:35,749
As a team.

1693
01:36:35,832 --> 01:36:37,334
This is it.

1694
01:36:38,710 --> 01:36:41,380
This is our moment.

1695
01:36:43,423 --> 01:36:44,925
Time to fight.

1696
01:36:52,432 --> 01:36:55,394
Bad time to say this,
but I don't actually have a plan.

1697
01:36:56,853 --> 01:36:58,689
Tails, any ideas?

1698
01:36:58,772 --> 01:37:00,440
We have to find his weak spot.

1699
01:37:00,524 --> 01:37:02,150
I suggest the groin.

1700
01:37:02,234 --> 01:37:04,319
What? No. No!

1701
01:37:04,403 --> 01:37:06,989
Traditionally, yes,
the groin is the weakest spot.

1702
01:37:07,072 --> 01:37:09,116
Stop saying "groin."

1703
01:37:09,199 --> 01:37:10,993
[Robotnik] Hedgehog!

1704
01:37:11,076 --> 01:37:12,411
Look out!

1705
01:37:15,205 --> 01:37:17,708
I know what his weak spot is. It's me.

1706
01:37:17,791 --> 01:37:19,543
I'm the groin!

1707
01:37:20,419 --> 01:37:22,087
[Knuckles grunts]

1708
01:37:22,170 --> 01:37:23,213
- Think about it.
- Whoa!

1709
01:37:23,296 --> 01:37:25,132
I live rent-free in this dude's head.

1710
01:37:25,215 --> 01:37:27,050
So if I go out there and rile him up...

1711
01:37:27,134 --> 01:37:29,553
He'll focus on only you,
leaving himself open

1712
01:37:29,636 --> 01:37:31,888
to a flanking maneuver
from me and the fox!

1713
01:37:31,972 --> 01:37:34,725
Hedgehog, you are a brave
and noble warrior.

1714
01:37:34,808 --> 01:37:37,477
Go to your certain death with honor.

1715
01:37:37,561 --> 01:37:39,730
We're gonna have to work
on your pep talks, pal.

1716
01:37:39,813 --> 01:37:41,982
- [laughs] Yeah.
- Let's go.

1717
01:37:45,694 --> 01:37:47,320
All right, mustache.

1718
01:37:47,404 --> 01:37:50,240
You want me? Come and get me.

1719
01:37:50,323 --> 01:37:53,076
You don't tell me
about coming and getting.

1720
01:37:53,160 --> 01:37:55,537
I am on the cutting edge
of coming and getting!

1721
01:37:55,620 --> 01:37:57,539
Coming, getting.

1722
01:37:57,622 --> 01:38:01,793
Coming, getting. Coming, getting.
Coming, getting.

1723
01:38:04,379 --> 01:38:06,465
Oh, you're really heavy.

1724
01:38:06,548 --> 01:38:10,385
That's because I am
one million percent muscle. Faster, fox!

1725
01:38:12,596 --> 01:38:15,766
- Go! Move, guys! Move back!
- Let's go, that's it! Go, go, go!

1726
01:38:15,849 --> 01:38:16,892
- Keep going!
- Go! Go!

1727
01:38:16,975 --> 01:38:18,810
- No, no! Stop!
- Stop the truck!

1728
01:38:18,894 --> 01:38:20,228
Tom, what happened here?

1729
01:38:20,312 --> 01:38:23,190
- You thinking what I'm thinking?
- Let's go get our kid.

1730
01:38:23,273 --> 01:38:24,649
[both] We need your truck!

1731
01:38:30,864 --> 01:38:33,992
[voice slowing] Coming, getting. Whew!

1732
01:38:34,076 --> 01:38:35,911
[Sonic] Yoo-hoo!

1733
01:38:35,994 --> 01:38:37,454
- So what's the plan here?
- [panting]

1734
01:38:37,537 --> 01:38:38,580
Huh?

1735
01:38:38,663 --> 01:38:40,499
You gonna build a big robot house?

1736
01:38:40,582 --> 01:38:43,043
Get yourself a big robot wife?

1737
01:38:43,126 --> 01:38:47,464
I'm going to enslave humanity
and force them to service my machines.

1738
01:38:47,547 --> 01:38:50,383
First, Green Hills. Then the universe.

1739
01:38:50,467 --> 01:38:51,718
Then the multiverse.

1740
01:38:51,802 --> 01:38:54,513
Then who knows? Maybe that'll be enough.

1741
01:38:54,596 --> 01:38:56,473
Full disclosure?

1742
01:38:57,349 --> 01:38:59,935
You won't be there.

1743
01:39:04,481 --> 01:39:06,608
[grunts] Eye lasers? Really?

1744
01:39:15,200 --> 01:39:16,993
[panting]

1745
01:39:19,079 --> 01:39:21,039
Snot rocket!

1746
01:39:22,624 --> 01:39:23,667
No, no, no!

1747
01:39:25,210 --> 01:39:27,129
[screaming]

1748
01:39:29,005 --> 01:39:30,257
[grunts]

1749
01:39:30,340 --> 01:39:33,677
[laughing] Giving up already?

1750
01:39:33,760 --> 01:39:37,472
Not so tough when you're fighting someone
700 times your size, are ya?

1751
01:39:39,599 --> 01:39:42,060
You can't beat me!

1752
01:39:42,144 --> 01:39:45,355
I'm all-powerful! All-knowing!

1753
01:39:48,066 --> 01:39:50,277
All-seeing.

1754
01:39:51,403 --> 01:39:53,738
Looks like your fancy robot has a glitch.

1755
01:39:53,822 --> 01:39:56,032
[voice multiplying] Is it me?
What about me? I'm over here.

1756
01:39:56,116 --> 01:39:57,993
Up top! Down below! Behind you! [laughs]

1757
01:39:58,076 --> 01:39:59,995
[voices overlapping] I'm over here.
Sorry! Over here.

1758
01:40:00,078 --> 01:40:01,830
Too slow! Try again.

1759
01:40:01,913 --> 01:40:03,957
You can't outsmart me. Missed me again.

1760
01:40:04,040 --> 01:40:05,125
I'm the outsmarter-er!

1761
01:40:05,208 --> 01:40:06,251
[grunts]

1762
01:40:06,334 --> 01:40:08,336
[yelping]

1763
01:40:10,172 --> 01:40:13,133
I didn't outsmart you.
I'm just the distraction.

1764
01:40:13,216 --> 01:40:14,426
[Knuckles] Robotnik!

1765
01:40:15,135 --> 01:40:17,888
I am also a hologram.

1766
01:40:17,971 --> 01:40:19,890
Disloyal.

1767
01:40:19,973 --> 01:40:22,809
"Dis" is how I roll.

1768
01:40:23,935 --> 01:40:25,520
[yells]

1769
01:40:25,604 --> 01:40:27,314
[Robotnik groaning]

1770
01:40:36,781 --> 01:40:39,492
[both screaming]

1771
01:40:43,038 --> 01:40:44,873
[both grunting]

1772
01:40:47,375 --> 01:40:49,920
[gasping]

1773
01:40:51,213 --> 01:40:52,756
Where's my Emerald?

1774
01:40:53,506 --> 01:40:55,383
No, no, no, no!

1775
01:40:55,467 --> 01:40:57,802
Computer, auxiliary power.

1776
01:41:01,598 --> 01:41:03,225
[groans]

1777
01:41:05,227 --> 01:41:07,062
[gasps] Oh.

1778
01:41:07,145 --> 01:41:09,856
The Emerald. It's right there.

1779
01:41:09,940 --> 01:41:11,858
Move, you hunk of junk!

1780
01:41:16,404 --> 01:41:19,783
I have to... [groans] ...reach it.

1781
01:41:20,742 --> 01:41:22,369
[groaning]

1782
01:41:25,163 --> 01:41:26,414
[grunts]

1783
01:41:43,014 --> 01:41:44,015
Come on.

1784
01:41:46,184 --> 01:41:48,353
There he is! Go! Go, go, go!

1785
01:41:54,859 --> 01:41:56,319
[Maddie yelling]

1786
01:41:57,279 --> 01:41:58,321
No!

1787
01:41:58,405 --> 01:41:59,698
We got you, Sonic.

1788
01:42:00,907 --> 01:42:02,325
Hold on!

1789
01:42:10,875 --> 01:42:13,420
[all panting]

1790
01:42:15,547 --> 01:42:17,799
- You guys okay?
- [Tom grunts] Yeah.

1791
01:42:19,301 --> 01:42:20,468
Okay.

1792
01:42:25,890 --> 01:42:27,934
I got the Emerald.
We could still defeat him.

1793
01:42:28,018 --> 01:42:30,061
Come on, come on.
How does this thing work?

1794
01:42:30,145 --> 01:42:31,187
What do I do?

1795
01:42:31,271 --> 01:42:32,314
[cracking]

1796
01:42:32,397 --> 01:42:34,149
What?

1797
01:42:34,232 --> 01:42:36,943
No. No, no, no!

1798
01:42:40,822 --> 01:42:44,993
Look at the happy little family.

1799
01:42:50,874 --> 01:42:53,376
You have to get away from me.
I'm the one he wants.

1800
01:42:53,460 --> 01:42:54,878
Hey.

1801
01:42:54,961 --> 01:42:56,588
We're not going anywhere.

1802
01:42:56,671 --> 01:42:58,340
We're family.

1803
01:43:01,926 --> 01:43:03,595
And families stick together...

1804
01:43:06,473 --> 01:43:07,682
no matter what.

1805
01:43:10,810 --> 01:43:11,936
I love you guys.

1806
01:43:12,854 --> 01:43:14,397
We love you too, Sonic.

1807
01:43:14,481 --> 01:43:16,649
[chaos emeralds chiming]

1808
01:43:22,906 --> 01:43:24,366
No!

1809
01:43:26,409 --> 01:43:28,578
I got him!

1810
01:43:28,661 --> 01:43:34,501
I finally got him! [cackles]

1811
01:43:34,584 --> 01:43:36,252
[thudding]

1812
01:43:37,712 --> 01:43:39,464
What was that?

1813
01:44:08,159 --> 01:44:09,869
[gasps]

1814
01:44:12,414 --> 01:44:13,748
[yelps]

1815
01:44:19,170 --> 01:44:22,257
[panting]

1816
01:44:25,343 --> 01:44:27,554
It's over, Eggman.

1817
01:44:27,637 --> 01:44:31,307
[chuckles] I like the new look.
It works for you.

1818
01:44:32,225 --> 01:44:35,228
What do you say
we just let bygones be bygones?

1819
01:44:35,311 --> 01:44:37,188
I did some things, you did some things.

1820
01:44:37,272 --> 01:44:39,065
There are good people on both sides.

1821
01:44:40,775 --> 01:44:43,862
Surely two intelligent beings...

1822
01:44:45,613 --> 01:44:47,615
can work these things out!

1823
01:44:54,789 --> 01:44:56,332
[grunts]

1824
01:44:59,627 --> 01:45:00,670
Come on, buddy.

1825
01:45:00,753 --> 01:45:02,088
- Get him, Sonic!
- Come on.

1826
01:45:02,172 --> 01:45:03,506
Yeah. Come on.

1827
01:45:07,510 --> 01:45:09,012
[gasping]

1828
01:45:20,064 --> 01:45:21,524
Oh, it's like that?

1829
01:45:23,026 --> 01:45:25,320
Okay, we're not friends.

1830
01:45:29,741 --> 01:45:32,035
Later, hater!

1831
01:45:43,421 --> 01:45:45,381
- Sonic!
- Buddy! [laughs]

1832
01:45:45,465 --> 01:45:47,509
Wait! You cannot touch him!

1833
01:45:47,592 --> 01:45:50,261
The hedgehog holds
the power of the Emerald.

1834
01:45:50,345 --> 01:45:54,557
I am sorry.
He is no longer the Sonic you once knew.

1835
01:45:55,141 --> 01:45:56,142
What?

1836
01:46:11,407 --> 01:46:13,284
[sniffs]

1837
01:46:14,661 --> 01:46:15,912
Mmm.

1838
01:46:15,995 --> 01:46:17,705
Oh, you got to try this.

1839
01:46:23,461 --> 01:46:26,798
Okay. He is exactly
the Sonic you once knew.

1840
01:46:28,675 --> 01:46:30,051
- Uh-huh.
- Uh-huh.

1841
01:46:38,518 --> 01:46:40,144
- Sonic!
- Whoa!

1842
01:46:41,896 --> 01:46:43,481
Bring it in, bud.

1843
01:46:44,941 --> 01:46:46,901
It's good to be back in blue.

1844
01:46:46,985 --> 01:46:48,361
The golden god thing was fun,

1845
01:46:48,444 --> 01:46:50,321
but blue has always been more my color.

1846
01:46:50,405 --> 01:46:51,489
Looks good on you.

1847
01:46:51,573 --> 01:46:54,325
Sonic, you were the most powerful hero

1848
01:46:54,409 --> 01:46:56,995
in the universe, and you let it go.

1849
01:46:57,078 --> 01:46:58,162
Why?

1850
01:46:59,914 --> 01:47:03,042
Because I still have
some growing up to do.

1851
01:47:05,295 --> 01:47:07,589
And I kind of like being a kid.

1852
01:47:07,672 --> 01:47:09,549
And you're not just any kid.

1853
01:47:09,632 --> 01:47:11,509
You're our kid.

1854
01:47:11,593 --> 01:47:13,011
That's right.

1855
01:47:13,094 --> 01:47:15,805
- Bring it in!
- [Tails] Yay. Hugs.

1856
01:47:15,888 --> 01:47:17,348
It's a good thing
we didn't do this before.

1857
01:47:17,432 --> 01:47:18,725
You would've blown up.

1858
01:47:26,357 --> 01:47:27,942
[Sonic] Whoa! You fixed it.

1859
01:47:28,026 --> 01:47:31,362
I've spent my whole life
questing for this.

1860
01:47:31,446 --> 01:47:32,739
Now I have it.

1861
01:47:32,822 --> 01:47:34,616
Now we have it.

1862
01:47:34,699 --> 01:47:37,285
What do we do with it? What next?

1863
01:47:37,368 --> 01:47:39,495
There were once two orders of heroes

1864
01:47:39,579 --> 01:47:43,708
who protected the galaxy from those
who would use the Emerald for evil.

1865
01:47:43,791 --> 01:47:47,670
But they have all passed on
to the great battleground in the sky.

1866
01:47:47,754 --> 01:47:51,215
So we start a new order. The three of us.

1867
01:47:51,299 --> 01:47:53,009
This is no light task.

1868
01:47:53,092 --> 01:47:57,722
We must make a vow to use our powers
to keep the universe safe,

1869
01:47:58,556 --> 01:48:00,391
to watch out for each other.

1870
01:48:00,475 --> 01:48:02,185
Our new tribe.

1871
01:48:02,268 --> 01:48:03,394
Oh, I know!

1872
01:48:03,478 --> 01:48:04,854
A power bump!

1873
01:48:04,937 --> 01:48:06,856
Good idea.

1874
01:48:06,939 --> 01:48:10,151
It's an Earth custom.
An unbreakable promise.

1875
01:48:10,234 --> 01:48:12,028
Very well.

1876
01:48:12,820 --> 01:48:15,239
A power bump it is.

1877
01:48:16,407 --> 01:48:18,076
Power bump!

1878
01:48:21,996 --> 01:48:23,748
[Sonic over PA] It's truly a beautiful day

1879
01:48:23,831 --> 01:48:26,125
for baseball here in Green Hills.

1880
01:48:26,209 --> 01:48:27,919
An exciting lineup today

1881
01:48:28,002 --> 01:48:31,297
with the debut appearance
of two new players!

1882
01:48:31,381 --> 01:48:35,551
On the mound, rookie sensation
from across the galaxy,

1883
01:48:35,635 --> 01:48:38,179
Miles "Tails" Prower,

1884
01:48:38,262 --> 01:48:43,393
facing off against the powerhouse,
Knuckles the Echidna.

1885
01:48:43,476 --> 01:48:46,312
Um, I don't understand.

1886
01:48:46,396 --> 01:48:48,564
Why am I angry at the enemy ball?

1887
01:48:48,648 --> 01:48:49,816
You're not angry.

1888
01:48:49,899 --> 01:48:51,734
You just want to hit it as hard as you can

1889
01:48:51,818 --> 01:48:53,152
and then run around the bases.

1890
01:48:53,236 --> 01:48:56,322
But if my quest ends where I am standing,

1891
01:48:56,406 --> 01:48:57,990
why run at all?

1892
01:48:58,074 --> 01:49:01,077
Ugh. I can't with this guy.
Why do I even try?

1893
01:49:01,160 --> 01:49:03,830
This is just a game.
We're out here having fun.

1894
01:49:03,913 --> 01:49:05,415
Just having some fun.

1895
01:49:05,498 --> 01:49:08,042
Fun. Huh.

1896
01:49:08,126 --> 01:49:10,503
All right! Give him the heat, Tails!

1897
01:49:10,586 --> 01:49:12,505
Hope you're ready for my fastball.

1898
01:49:12,588 --> 01:49:15,049
Your fastball will be dishonored.

1899
01:49:15,133 --> 01:49:17,385
And so will you, fox. [grunts]

1900
01:49:17,468 --> 01:49:18,594
Easy, guys!

1901
01:49:18,678 --> 01:49:20,054
Don't think about it too much.

1902
01:49:20,138 --> 01:49:22,098
Just keep your elbow up, eye on the ball

1903
01:49:22,181 --> 01:49:23,349
and give it a ride.

1904
01:49:23,433 --> 01:49:24,851
A ride? To where?

1905
01:49:25,727 --> 01:49:26,728
[grunts]

1906
01:49:26,811 --> 01:49:28,104
[growls]

1907
01:49:29,105 --> 01:49:30,398
Power bump!

1908
01:49:32,692 --> 01:49:34,110
[screams]

1909
01:49:34,861 --> 01:49:37,155
Ha! Victory is mine!

1910
01:49:37,238 --> 01:49:39,782
Hey, no fair! That shouldn't count.

1911
01:49:39,866 --> 01:49:42,118
First base is also mine!

1912
01:49:42,201 --> 01:49:43,911
- I think that was our only ball.
- [laughs]

1913
01:49:43,995 --> 01:49:46,789
- I have conquered the second of the bases!
- All right.

1914
01:49:46,873 --> 01:49:48,416
Who wants ice cream?

1915
01:49:48,499 --> 01:49:49,709
Knocked the cover off that.

1916
01:49:49,792 --> 01:49:52,253
- Ice cream!
- Ice cream, yeah!

1917
01:49:52,336 --> 01:49:56,424
[laughing] I am having the fun!
What is ice cream?

1918
01:49:56,507 --> 01:49:59,844
It's a dessert.
If you like fun, you're gonna love it.

1919
01:49:59,927 --> 01:50:03,097
Oh, yum. Dessert.
Does it have grapes in it?

1920
01:50:03,181 --> 01:50:04,766
No, not usually.

1921
01:50:04,849 --> 01:50:07,310
I'm proud of our little guy.

1922
01:50:07,393 --> 01:50:10,855
I really like his new friends,
especially the red one.

1923
01:50:10,938 --> 01:50:13,566
- He cracks me up.
- Heck of a swing too.

1924
01:50:13,649 --> 01:50:14,901
Come on, fox.

1925
01:50:14,984 --> 01:50:16,611
- Our dessert adventure awaits.
- Whoo!

1926
01:50:16,694 --> 01:50:17,820
- Good job, guys.
- Yeah.

1927
01:50:17,904 --> 01:50:19,071
You too, baby.

1928
01:50:19,155 --> 01:50:21,324
Let's go get some ice cream.
Come on, come on.

1929
01:50:22,366 --> 01:50:24,535
I'm happy for you, pal.

1930
01:50:24,619 --> 01:50:26,204
Got your wingmen.

1931
01:50:26,287 --> 01:50:27,789
Perfect friends to grow up with.

1932
01:50:27,872 --> 01:50:31,167
- Come on, Knuckles.
- Ah! My victory chariot!

1933
01:50:33,211 --> 01:50:36,172
I've got a lot more than that... Dad.

1934
01:50:41,636 --> 01:50:42,970
Race you to the truck.

1935
01:50:44,639 --> 01:50:46,057
One, two, three, go!

1936
01:50:46,140 --> 01:50:48,768
No, don't go easy on me. I want your best.

1937
01:50:48,851 --> 01:50:51,813
Sonic, I have just been told
they have sprinkles.

1938
01:50:51,896 --> 01:50:55,566
Ice cream and sprinkles?
This is your new destiny.

1939
01:50:55,650 --> 01:51:00,571
What a perfect meal to celebrate
my victory over you in base of ball.

1940
01:51:00,655 --> 01:51:03,366
- What?
- I mean, you barely beat me.

1941
01:51:03,449 --> 01:51:06,452
Ha! You've never been beaten so hard.

1942
